metadata:

hadiths[136]{hadithnumber,arabic,bengali,english,french,indonesian,russian,urdu,grades,reference,international_number,narrator_chain,chapter_intro}:
{"hadithnumber": "469", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو بَكْرِ بْنُ أَبِي شَيْبَةَ، حَدَّثَنَا يُونُسُ بْنُ مُحَمَّدٍ، حَدَّثَنَا لَيْثُ بْنُ سَعْدٍ، ح وَحَدَّثَنَا أَبُو بَكْرِ بْنُ أَبِي شَيْبَةَ، حَدَّثَنَا دَاوُدُ بْنُ عَبْدِ اللَّهِ الْجَعْفَرِيُّ، عَنْ عَبْدِ الْعَزِيزِ بْنِ مُحَمَّدٍ، جَمِيعًا عَنْ يَزِيدَ بْنِ عَبْدِ اللَّهِ بْنِ أُسَامَةَ بْنِ الْهَادِ، عَنِ الْوَلِيدِ بْنِ أَبِي الْوَلِيدِ، عَنْ عُثْمَانَ بْنِ عَبْدِ اللَّهِ بْنِ سُرَاقَةَ الْعَدَوِيِّ، عَنْ عُمَرَ بْنِ الْخَطَّابِ، قَالَ سَمِعْتُ رَسُولَ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ يَقُولُ ‏ ‏ مَنْ بَنَى مَسْجِدًا يُذْكَرُ فِيهِ اسْمُ اللَّهِ بَنَى اللَّهُ لَهُ بَيْتًا فِي الْجَنَّةِ ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "\"I heard the Messenger of Allah say: 'Whoever builds a mosque in which the Name of Allah is mentioned, Allah will build a house for him in Paradise.'\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated that 'Umar bin Khattab said:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "470", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ بَشَّارٍ، حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو بَكْرٍ الْحَنَفِيُّ، حَدَّثَنَا عَبْدُ الْحَمِيدِ بْنُ جَعْفَرٍ، عَنْ أَبِيهِ، عَنْ مَحْمُودِ بْنِ لَبِيدٍ، عَنْ عُثْمَانَ بْنِ عَفَّانَ، قَالَ سَمِعْتُ رَسُولَ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ يَقُولُ ‏ ‏ مَنْ بَنَى لِلَّهِ مَسْجِدًا بَنَى اللَّهُ لَهُ مِثْلَهُ فِي الْجَنَّةِ ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "\"I heard the Messenger of Allah say: 'Whoever builds a mosque for the sake of Allah, Allah will build something similar for him in Paradise.'\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated that 'Uthman bin 'Affan said:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "471", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا الْعَبَّاسُ بْنُ عُثْمَانَ الدِّمَشْقِيُّ، حَدَّثَنَا الْوَلِيدُ بْنُ مُسْلِمٍ، عَنِ ابْنِ لَهِيعَةَ، حَدَّثَنِي أَبُو الأَسْوَدِ، عَنْ عُرْوَةَ، عَنْ عَلِيِّ بْنِ أَبِي طَالِبٍ، قَالَ قَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ ‏ ‏ مَنْ بَنَى لِلَّهِ مَسْجِدًا مِنْ مَالِهِ بَنَى اللَّهُ لَهُ بَيْتًا فِي الْجَنَّةِ ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "\"The Messenger of Allah said: 'Whoever builds a mosque for the sake of Allah (from his own wealth), Allah will build a house for him in Paradise.'\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated that 'Ali bin Abu Talib said:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "472", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا يُونُسُ بْنُ عَبْدِ الأَعْلَى، حَدَّثَنَا عَبْدُ اللَّهِ بْنُ وَهْبٍ، عَنْ إِبْرَاهِيمَ بْنِ نَشِيطٍ، عَنْ عَبْدِ اللَّهِ بْنِ عَبْدِ الرَّحْمَنِ بْنِ أَبِي حُسَيْنٍ النَّوْفَلِيِّ، عَنْ عَطَاءِ بْنِ أَبِي رَبَاحٍ، عَنْ جَابِرِ بْنِ عَبْدِ اللَّهِ، أَنَّ رَسُولَ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ قَالَ ‏ ‏ مَنْ بَنَى مَسْجِدًا لِلَّهِ كَمَفْحَصِ قَطَاةٍ أَوْ أَصْغَرَ بَنَى اللَّهُ لَهُ بَيْتًا فِي الْجَنَّةِ ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "The Messenger of Allah said: \"Whoever builds a mosque for the sake of Allah, like a sparrow's nest for Allah or even smaller, Allah will build for him a house in Paradise.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated from Jabir bin 'Abdullah that:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "473", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا عَبْدُ اللَّهِ بْنُ مُعَاوِيَةَ الْجُمَحِيُّ، حَدَّثَنَا حَمَّادُ بْنُ سَلَمَةَ، عَنْ أَيُّوبَ، عَنْ أَبِي قِلاَبَةَ، عَنْ أَنَسِ بْنِ مَالِكٍ، قَالَ قَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ ‏ ‏ لاَ تَقُومُ السَّاعَةُ حَتَّى يَتَبَاهَى النَّاسُ فِي الْمَسَاجِدِ ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "\"The Messenger of Allah said: 'The Hour will not begin until the people compete in (building) mosques.'\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated that Anas bin Malik said:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "474", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا جُبَارَةُ بْنُ الْمُغَلِّسِ، حَدَّثَنَا عَبْدُ الْكَرِيمِ بْنُ عَبْدِ الرَّحْمَنِ الْبَجَلِيُّ، عَنْ لَيْثٍ، عَنْ عِكْرِمَةَ، عَنِ ابْنِ عَبَّاسٍ، قَالَ قَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ ‏ ‏ أَرَاكُمْ سَتُشَرِّفُونَ مَسَاجِدَكُمْ بَعْدِي كَمَا شَرَّفَتِ الْيَهُودُ كَنَائِسَهَا وَكَمَا شَرَّفَتِ النَّصَارَى بِيَعَهَا ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "The Messenger of Allah said: \"I see you building your mosque high after I am gone, just as the Jews built their synagogues high and the Christians built their churches high.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated that Ibn 'Abbas said:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "475", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا جُبَارَةُ بْنُ الْمُغَلِّسِ، حَدَّثَنَا عَبْدُ الْكَرِيمِ بْنُ عَبْدِ الرَّحْمَنِ، عَنْ أَبِي إِسْحَاقَ، عَنْ عَمْرِو بْنِ مَيْمُونٍ، عَنْ عُمَرَ بْنِ الْخَطَّابِ، قَالَ قَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ ‏ ‏ مَا سَاءَ عَمَلُ قَوْمٍ قَطُّ إِلاَّ زَخْرَفُوا مَسَاجِدَهُمْ ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "The Messenger of Allah said: \"No people's deeds ever became evil deeds but they started to adorn their places of worship.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated that 'Umar bin Khattab said:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "476", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا عَلِيُّ بْنُ مُحَمَّدٍ، حَدَّثَنَا وَكِيعٌ، عَنْ حَمَّادِ بْنِ سَلَمَةَ، عَنْ أَبِي التَّيَّاحِ الضُّبَعِيِّ، عَنْ أَنَسِ بْنِ مَالِكٍ، قَالَ كَانَ مَوْضِعُ مَسْجِدِ النَّبِيِّ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ لِبَنِي النَّجَّارِ وَكَانَ فِيهِ نَخْلٌ وَمَقَابِرُ لِلْمُشْرِكِينَ فَقَالَ لَهُمُ النَّبِيُّ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ ‏\"‏ ثَامِنُونِي بِهِ ‏\"‏ ‏.‏ قَالُوا لاَ نَأْخُذُ لَهُ ثَمَنًا أَبَدًا ‏.‏ قَالَ فَكَانَ النَّبِيُّ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ يَبْنِيهِ وَهُمْ يُنَاوِلُونَهُ وَالنَّبِيُّ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ يَقُولُ ‏\"‏ أَلاَ إِنَّ الْعَيْشَ عَيْشُ الآخِرَةِ فَاغْفِرْ لِلأَنْصَارِ وَالْمُهَاجِرَةِ ‏\"‏ ‏.‏ قَالَ وَكَانَ النَّبِيُّ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ يُصَلِّي قَبْلَ أَنْ يَبْنِيَ الْمَسْجِدَ حَيْثُ أَدْرَكَتْهُ الصَّلاَةُ ‏.‏", "bengali": "", "english": "\"The location where the Prophet's Mosque was built belonged to Banu Najjar. In it there were date-palm trees and graves of the idolaters. The Prophet said to them: 'Name its price.' They said: 'We will never take any money for it.' The Prophet built it and they were assisting him, and the Prophet was saying: 'The real life is the life of the Hereafter so forgive the Ansar and the Muhajirah.' Before the mosque was built, the Prophet would perform prayer wherever he was when the time for prayer came.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "عبداللہ بن عباس رضی اللہ عنہما کہتے ہیں کہ  آپ یعنی نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کا یہ سونا بیٹھے بیٹ", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "476", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated that Anas bin Malik said:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "477", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ يَحْيَى، حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو هَمَّامٍ الدَّلاَّلُ، حَدَّثَنَا سَعِيدُ بْنُ السَّائِبِ، عَنْ مُحَمَّدِ بْنِ عَبْدِ اللَّهِ بْنِ عِيَاضٍ، عَنْ عُثْمَانَ بْنِ أَبِي الْعَاصِ، أَنَّ رَسُولَ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ أَمَرَهُ أَنْ يَجْعَلَ مَسْجِدَ الطَّائِفِ حَيْثُ كَانَ طَاغِيَتُهُمْ ‏.‏", "bengali": "", "english": "The Messenger of Allah commanded him to build the mosque of Ta'if  in the place where the Taghuts used to be.", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "علی بن ابی طالب رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  آنکھ سرین کا بند", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "477", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated from 'Uthman bin Abul-'As that:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "478", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ يَحْيَى، حَدَّثَنَا عَمْرُو بْنُ عُثْمَانَ، حَدَّثَنَا مُوسَى بْنُ أَعْيَنَ، حَدَّثَنَا مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ إِسْحَاقَ، عَنْ نَافِعٍ، عَنِ ابْنِ عُمَرَ، وَسُئِلَ، عَنِ الْحِيطَانِ، تُلْقَى فِيهَا الْعَذِرَاتُ فَقَالَ ‏ ‏ إِذَا سُقِيَتْ مِرَارًا فَصَلُّوا فِيهَا ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏ يَرْفَعُهُ إِلَى النَّبِيِّ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "He said: \"If it has been watered several times, then perform prayer there,\" and he attributed that to the Prophet.", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated that Ibn 'Umar was asked about gardens in which excrement was thrown.:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "479", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ يَحْيَى، حَدَّثَنَا يَزِيدُ بْنُ هَارُونَ، حَدَّثَنَا سُفْيَانُ، عَنْ عَمْرِو بْنِ يَحْيَى، عَنْ أَبِيهِ، وَحَمَّادُ بْنُ سَلَمَةَ، عَنْ عَمْرِو بْنِ يَحْيَى، عَنْ أَبِيهِ، عَنْ أَبِي سَعِيدٍ الْخُدْرِيِّ، قَالَ قَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ ‏ ‏ الأَرْضُ كُلُّهَا مَسْجِدٌ إِلاَّ الْمَقْبَرَةَ وَالْحَمَّامَ ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "\"The Messenger of Allah said: 'All the earth is a mosque, except for graveyards and Hammam.'\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated that Abu Sa'eed Khudri said:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "480", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ إِبْرَاهِيمَ الدِّمَشْقِيُّ، حَدَّثَنَا عَبْدُ اللَّهِ بْنُ يَزِيدَ، عَنْ يَحْيَى بْنِ أَيُّوبَ، عَنْ زَيْدِ بْنِ جَبِيرَةَ، عَنْ دَاوُدَ بْنِ الْحُصَيْنِ، عَنْ نَافِعٍ، عَنِ ابْنِ عُمَرَ، قَالَ نَهَى رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ أَنْ يُصَلَّى فِي سَبْعِ مَوَاطِنَ فِي الْمَزْبَلَةِ وَالْمَجْزَرَةِ وَالْمَقْبَرَةِ وَقَارِعَةِ الطَّرِيقِ وَالْحَمَّامِ وَمَعَاطِنِ الإِبِلِ وَفَوْقَ الْكَعْبَةِ ‏.‏", "bengali": "", "english": "\"Allah's Messenger prohibited prayer from being performed in seven places: The garbage dump, the slaughtering area, the graveyard, the commonly used road, the bathroom, in the area that camels rest at, and above the Ka'bah.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "جابر بن عبداللہ رضی اللہ عنہما کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  جب کوئی اپنی شر", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "480", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated that Ibn 'Umar said:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "481", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا عَلِيُّ بْنُ دَاوُدَ، وَمُحَمَّدُ بْنُ أَبِي الْحُسَيْنِ، قَالاَ حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو صَالِحٍ، حَدَّثَنِي اللَّيْثُ، حَدَّثَنِي نَافِعٌ، عَنِ ابْنِ عُمَرَ، عَنْ عُمَرَ بْنِ الْخَطَّابِ، أَنَّ رَسُولَ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ قَالَ ‏ ‏ سَبْعُ مَوَاطِنَ لاَ تَجُوزُ فِيهَا الصَّلاَةُ ظَاهِرُ بَيْتِ اللَّهِ وَالْمَقْبَرَةُ وَالْمَزْبَلَةُ وَالْمَجْزَرَةُ وَالْحَمَّامُ وَعَطَنُ الإِبِلِ وَمَحَجَّةُ الطَّرِيقِ ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "The Messenger of Allah said: \"There are seven places where it is not permissible to perform the prayer: The top of the House of Allah; graveyards; garbage dumps; slaughterhouses; bathrooms; the area that camels rest, and the main road.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated from 'Umar bin Khattab that:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "482", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا يَحْيَى بْنُ عُثْمَانَ بْنِ سَعِيدِ بْنِ كَثِيرِ بْنِ دِينَارٍ الْحِمْصِيُّ، حَدَّثَنَا مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ حِمْيَرَ، حَدَّثَنَا زَيْدُ بْنُ جَبِيرَةَ الأَنْصَارِيُّ، عَنْ دَاوُدَ بْنِ الْحُصَيْنِ، عَنْ نَافِعٍ، عَنِ ابْنِ عُمَرَ، عَنْ رَسُولِ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ قَالَ ‏ ‏ خِصَالٌ لاَ تَنْبَغِي فِي الْمَسْجِدِ لاَ يُتَّخَذُ طَرِيقًا وَلاَ يُشْهَرُ فِيهِ سِلاَحٌ وَلاَ يُنْبَضُ فِيهِ بِقَوْسٍ وَلاَ يُنْشَرُ فِيهِ نَبْلٌ وَلاَ يُمَرُّ فِيهِ بِلَحْمٍ نِيءٍ وَلاَ يُضْرَبُ فِيهِ حَدٌّ وَلاَ يُقْتَصُّ فِيهِ مِنْ أَحَدٍ وَلاَ يُتَّخَذُ سُوقًا ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "The Messenger of Allah said: \"There are things which are not befitting for the mosque: it should not be taken as a thoroughfare; weapons should not be unsheathed in it; bows should not be drawn nor arrows shot in it; no one should pass through it carrying raw meat; no prescribed punishment or retaliatory punishment should be carried out in it; and it should not be used as a marketplace.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated from Ibn 'Umar that:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "483", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا عَبْدُ اللَّهِ بْنُ سَعِيدٍ الْكِنْدِيُّ، حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو خَالِدٍ الأَحْمَرُ، عَنِ ابْنِ عَجْلاَنَ، عَنْ عَمْرِو بْنِ شُعَيْبٍ، عَنْ أَبِيهِ، عَنْ جَدِّهِ، قَالَ نَهَى رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ عَنِ الْبَيْعِ وَالاِبْتِيَاعِ وَعَنْ تَنَاشُدِ الأَشْعَارِ فِي الْمَسَاجِدِ ‏.‏", "bengali": "", "english": "\"The Messenger of Allah forbade buying and selling in the mosque, and reciting poetry in the mosque.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "طلق رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  میں نے رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم سے سنا: آپ سے شرمگاہ چھونے کے بارے", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "483", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated from 'Amr bin Shu'aib from his father that his grandfather said:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "484", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا أَحْمَدُ بْنُ يُوسُفَ السُّلَمِيُّ، حَدَّثَنَا مُسْلِمُ بْنُ إِبْرَاهِيمَ، حَدَّثَنَا الْحَارِثُ بْنُ نَبْهَانَ، حَدَّثَنَا عُتْبَةُ بْنُ يَقْظَانَ، عَنْ أَبِي سَعِيدٍ، عَنْ مَكْحُولٍ، عَنْ وَاثِلَةَ بْنِ الأَسْقَعِ، أَنَّ النَّبِيَّ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ قَالَ ‏ ‏ جَنِّبُوا مَسَاجِدَكُمْ صِبْيَانَكُمْ وَمَجَانِينَكُمْ وَشِرَارَكُمْ وَبَيْعَكُمْ وَخُصُومَاتِكُمْ وَرَفْعَ أَصْوَاتِكُمْ وَإِقَامَةَ حُدُودِكُمْ وَسَلَّ سُيُوفِكُمْ وَاتَّخِذُوا عَلَى أَبْوَابِهَا الْمَطَاهِرَ وَجَمِّرُوهَا فِي الْجُمَعِ ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "The Prophet said: \"Keep your infants, your insane and your evil ones away from your mosques. Avoid engaging in transactions and disputes, raising your voices, carrying out your prescribed punishments and unsheathing your swords therein. Make places for purification at their gates, and perfume them with incense on Fridays.\" (Maudu')", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated from Wathilah bin Asqa' that:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "485", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا إِسْحَاقُ بْنُ مَنْصُورٍ، حَدَّثَنَا عَبْدُ اللَّهِ بْنُ نُمَيْرٍ، أَنْبَأَنَا عُبَيْدُ اللَّهِ بْنُ عُمَرَ، عَنْ نَافِعٍ، عَنِ ابْنِ عُمَرَ، قَالَ كُنَّا نَنَامُ فِي الْمَسْجِدِ عَلَى عَهْدِ رَسُولِ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ ‏.‏", "bengali": "", "english": "\"We used to sleep in the mosque at the time of the Messenger of Allah.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "ابوہریرہ رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت ہے کہ  نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  آگ پر پکی ہوئی چیزوں", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "485", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated that Ibn 'Umar said:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "486", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو بَكْرِ بْنُ أَبِي شَيْبَةَ، حَدَّثَنَا الْحَسَنُ بْنُ مُوسَى، حَدَّثَنَا شَيْبَانُ بْنُ عَبْدِ الرَّحْمَنِ، عَنْ يَحْيَى بْنِ أَبِي كَثِيرٍ، عَنْ أَبِي سَلَمَةَ بْنِ عَبْدِ الرَّحْمَنِ، أَنَّ يَعِيشَ بْنَ قَيْسِ بْنِ طِخْفَةَ، حَدَّثَهُ عَنْ أَبِيهِ، وَكَانَ، مِنْ أَصْحَابِ الصُّفَّةِ قَالَ قَالَ لَنَا رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ ‏\"‏ انْطَلِقُوا ‏\"‏ ‏.‏ فَانْطَلَقْنَا إِلَى بَيْتِ عَائِشَةَ وَأَكَلْنَا وَشَرِبْنَا فَقَالَ لَنَا رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ ‏\"‏ إِنْ شِئْتُمْ نِمْتُمْ هَاهُنَا وَإِنْ شِئْتُمُ انْطَلَقْتُمْ إِلَى الْمَسْجِدِ ‏\"‏ ‏.‏ قَالَ فَقُلْنَا بَلْ نَنْطَلِقُ إِلَى الْمَسْجِدِ ‏.‏", "bengali": "", "english": "\"The Messenger of Allah said to us: 'Come with me.' So we went to the house of 'Aishah, where we ate and drank. Then the Messenger of Allah said to us: 'If you want, you can sleep here, or if you want you can go out to the mosque.' We said: 'We will go out to the mosque.'\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "ام المؤمنین عائشہ رضی اللہ عنہا کہتی ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  ہر اس چیز کے ا", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "486", "narrator_chain": "Ya'ish bin Qais bin Tikhfah narrated that his father, who was one of the people of Suffah, said:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "487", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا عَلِيُّ بْنُ مَيْمُونٍ الرَّقِّيُّ، حَدَّثَنَا مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ عُبَيْدٍ، ح وَحَدَّثَنَا عَلِيُّ بْنُ مُحَمَّدٍ، حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو مُعَاوِيَةَ، عَنِ الأَعْمَشِ، عَنْ إِبْرَاهِيمَ التَّيْمِيِّ، عَنْ أَبِيهِ، عَنْ أَبِي ذَرٍّ الْغِفَارِيِّ، قَالَ قُلْتُ يَا رَسُولَ اللَّهِ أَىُّ مَسْجِدٍ وُضِعَ أَوَّلُ قَالَ ‏\"‏ الْمَسْجِدُ الْحَرَامُ ‏\"‏ ‏.‏ قَالَ قُلْتُ ثُمَّ أَىٌّ قَالَ ‏\"‏ ثُمَّ الْمَسْجِدُ الأَقْصَى ‏\"‏ ‏.‏ قُلْتُ كَمْ بَيْنَهُمَا قَالَ ‏\"‏ أَرْبَعُونَ عَامًا ثُمَّ الأَرْضُ لَكَ مُصَلًّى فَصَلِّ حَيْثُ مَا أَدْرَكَتْكَ الصَّلاَةُ ‏\"‏ ‏.‏", "bengali": "", "english": "\"I said: 'O Messenger of Allah! Which mosque was built first?' He said: 'Al-Masjid Al-Haram (in Makkah).' I said: 'Then which?' He said: 'then Al-Masjid Al-Aqsa (in Jerusalem).' I said: 'How many years between them?' He said: 'Forty years, but the whole earth is a mosque for you, so pray wherever you are when the time for prayer comes.'\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "انس بن مالک رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت ہے  وہ اپنے دونوں ہاتھ اپنے دونوں کانوں پر رکھتے اور کہتے: یہ دونو", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "487", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated that Abu Dharr Al-Ghifari said:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "488", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو مَرْوَانَ، مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ عُثْمَانَ حَدَّثَنَا إِبْرَاهِيمُ بْنُ سَعْدٍ، عَنِ ابْنِ شِهَابٍ، عَنْ مَحْمُودِ بْنِ الرَّبِيعِ الأَنْصَارِيِّ، - وَكَانَ قَدْ عَقَلَ مَجَّةً مَجَّهَا رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ مِنْ دَلْوٍ فِي بِئْرٍ لَهُمْ - عَنْ عِتْبَانَ بْنِ مَالِكٍ السَّالِمِيِّ - وَكَانَ إِمَامَ قَوْمِهِ بَنِي سَالِمٍ وَكَانَ شَهِدَ بَدْرًا مَعَ رَسُولِ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ - قَالَ جِئْتُ رَسُولَ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ فَقُلْتُ يَا رَسُولَ اللَّهِ إِنِّي قَدْ أَنْكَرْتُ مِنْ بَصَرِي وَإِنَّ السَّيْلَ يَأْتِينِي فَيَحُولُ بَيْنِي وَبَيْنَ مَسْجِدِ قَوْمِي وَيَشُقُّ عَلَىَّ اجْتِيَازُهُ فَإِنْ رَأَيْتَ أَنْ تَأْتِيَنِي فَتُصَلِّيَ فِي بَيْتِي مَكَانًا أَتَّخِذُهُ مُصَلًّى فَافْعَلْ ‏.‏ قَالَ ‏\"‏ أَفْعَلُ ‏\"‏ ‏.‏ فَغَدَا عَلَىَّ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ وَأَبُو بَكْرٍ بَعْدَ مَا اشْتَدَّ النَّهَارُ وَاسْتَأْذَنَ فَأَذِنْتُ لَهُ وَلَمْ يَجْلِسْ حَتَّى قَالَ ‏\"‏ أَيْنَ تُحِبُّ أَنْ أُصَلِّيَ لَكَ مِنْ بَيْتِكَ ‏\"‏ ‏.‏ فَأَشَرْتُ لَهُ إِلَى الْمَكَانِ الَّذِي أُحِبُّ أَنْ أُصَلِّيَ فِيهِ فَقَامَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ وَصَفَفْنَا خَلْفَهُ فَصَلَّى بِنَا رَكْعَتَيْنِ ثُمَّ احْتَبَسْتُهُ عَلَى خَزِيرَةٍ تُصْنَعُ لَهُمْ ‏.‏", "bengali": "", "english": "'Itban bin Malik As-Salimi who was the chief of his people Banu Salim and had participated in (the battle of) Badr with the Messenger of Allah said: \"I came to the Messenger of Allah and said: 'O Messenger of Allah, my sight is failing and the flood comes and prevents me from reaching the mosque of my people, and it is too hard for me to cross the water. Do you think you could come and perform prayer in my house in a place which I can then take as a place of prayer?' He said: 'I will do that.' The following day, the Messenger of Allah and Abu Bakr came, when the heat of the day had grown intense. He asked permission to enter, and I gave him permission. He did not sit down until he said: 'Where would you like me to perform prayer for you in your house?' I showed him the place where I wanted him to pray, so the Messenger of Allah stood and we lined up behind him, and he led us in praying two Rak'ah (units). Then I asked him to stay and eat some Khazirah that had been prepared for them.'\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "عبداللہ بن عباس رضی اللہ عنہما کہتے ہیں کہ  نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے بکری کے دست کا گوشت کھایا", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "488", "narrator_chain": "Mahmud bin Rabi' Al-Ansari, who remembered that the Messenger of Allah spat a mouthful of water from a bucket into a well that belonged to them, narrated that :", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "489", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا يَحْيَى بْنُ الْفَضْلِ الْمُقْرِي، حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو عَامِرٍ، حَدَّثَنَا حَمَّادُ بْنُ سَلَمَةَ، عَنْ عَاصِمٍ، عَنْ أَبِي صَالِحٍ، عَنْ أَبِي هُرَيْرَةَ، أَنَّ رَجُلاً، مِنَ الأَنْصَارِ أَرْسَلَ إِلَى رَسُولِ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ أَنْ تَعَالَ فَخُطَّ لِي مَسْجِدًا فِي دَارِي أُصَلِّي فِيهِ وَذَلِكَ بَعْدَ مَا عَمِيَ فَجَاءَ فَفَعَلَ ‏.‏", "bengali": "", "english": "A man among the Ansar sent word to the Messenger of Allah saying: \"Come and designate a place in my house where I can perform prayer,' that was after he had become blind. So he went and did that.", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "جابر بن عبداللہ رضی اللہ عنہما کہتے ہیں کہ  نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم اور ابوبکرو عمر رضی اللہ عنہ", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "489", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated from Abu Hurairah that:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "490", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا يَحْيَى بْنُ حَكِيمٍ، حَدَّثَنَا ابْنُ أَبِي عَدِيٍّ، عَنِ ابْنِ عَوْنٍ، عَنْ أَنَسِ بْنِ سِيرِينَ، عَنْ عَبْدِ الْحَمِيدِ بْنِ الْمُنْذِرِ بْنِ الْجَارُودِ، عَنْ أَنَسِ بْنِ مَالِكٍ، قَالَ صَنَعَ بَعْضُ عُمُومَتِي لِلنَّبِيِّ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ طَعَامًا فَقَالَ لِلنَّبِيِّ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ إِنِّي أُحِبُّ أَنْ تَأْكُلَ فِي بَيْتِي وَتُصَلِّيَ فِيهِ ‏.‏ قَالَ فَأَتَاهُ وَفِي الْبَيْتِ فَحْلٌ مِنْ هَذِهِ الْفُحُولِ فَأَمَرَ بِنَاحِيَةٍ مِنْهُ فَكُنِسَ وَرُشَّ فَصَلَّى وَصَلَّيْنَا مَعَهُ ‏.‏ قَالَ أَبُو عَبْدِ اللَّهِ بْنُ مَاجَهْ الْفَحْلُ هُوَ الْحَصِيرُ الَّذِي قَدِ اسْوَدَّ ‏.‏", "bengali": "", "english": "\"One of my paternal uncles made some food for the Prophet and said to the Prophet: 'I would like you to eat and perform prayer in my house.' So he went to him, and in his house there was one of these Fahl. He ordered that a corner be swept and water sprinkled in it, then he performed prayer and we prayed with him.'\" (Sahih)Abu 'Abdullah bin Majah said: A Fahl is a mat that has become black (through use).", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "زہری کہتے ہیں کہ  میں ولید یا عبدالملک کے ساتھ شام کے کھانے پہ حاضر ہوا، جب نماز کا وقت ہوا تو میں و", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "490", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated that Anas bin Malik said:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "491", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا هِشَامُ بْنُ عَمَّارٍ، حَدَّثَنَا عَبْدُ الرَّحْمَنِ بْنُ سُلَيْمَانَ بْنِ أَبِي الْجَوْنِ، حَدَّثَنَا مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ صَالِحٍ الْمَدَنِيُّ، حَدَّثَنَا مُسْلِمُ بْنُ أَبِي مَرْيَمَ، عَنْ أَبِي سَعِيدٍ الْخُدْرِيِّ، قَالَ قَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ ‏ ‏ مَنْ أَخْرَجَ أَذًى مِنَ الْمَسْجِدِ بَنَى اللَّهُ لَهُ بَيْتًا فِي الْجَنَّةِ ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "\"The Messenger of Allah said: 'Whoever removes something harmful from the mosque, Allah will build for him a house in Paradise.'\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated that Abu Sa'eed Al-Khudri said:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "492", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا عَبْدُ الرَّحْمَنِ بْنُ بِشْرِ بْنِ الْحَكَمِ، وَأَحْمَدُ بْنُ الأَزْهَرِ، قَالاَ حَدَّثَنَا مَالِكُ بْنُ سُعَيْرٍ، أَنْبَأَنَا هِشَامُ بْنُ عُرْوَةَ، عَنْ أَبِيهِ، عَنْ عَائِشَةَ، أَنَّ رَسُولَ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ أَمَرَ بِالْمَسَاجِدِ أَنْ تُبْنَى فِي الدُّورِ وَأَنْ تُطَهَّرَ وَتُطَيَّبَ ‏.‏", "bengali": "", "english": "The Messenger of Allah commanded that mosque to be built in (Ad-Dur) villages, and that they be purified and perfumed.", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "سوید بن نعمان انصاری رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  وہ لوگ رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کے ساتھ خیبر کی ج", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "492", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated from 'Aishah that:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "493", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا رِزْقُ اللَّهِ بْنُ مُوسَى، حَدَّثَنَا يَعْقُوبُ بْنُ إِسْحَاقَ الْحَضْرَمِيُّ، حَدَّثَنَا زَائِدَةُ بْنُ قُدَامَةَ، عَنْ هِشَامِ بْنِ عُرْوَةَ، عَنْ أَبِيهِ، عَنْ عَائِشَةَ، قَالَتْ أَمَرَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ أَنْ تُتَّخَذَ الْمَسَاجِدُ فِي الدُّورِ وَأَنْ تُطَهَّرَ وَتُطَيَّبَ ‏.‏", "bengali": "", "english": "The Messenger of Allah commanded that places of prayer be established in villages, and that they be purified and perfumed.", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "ابوہریرہ رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے بکری کے دست کا گوشت کھایا، پھر کل", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "493", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated from 'Aishah that:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "494", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا أَحْمَدُ بْنُ سِنَانٍ، حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو مُعَاوِيَةَ، عَنْ خَالِدِ بْنِ إِيَاسٍ، عَنْ يَحْيَى بْنِ عَبْدِ الرَّحْمَنِ بْنِ حَاطِبٍ، عَنْ أَبِي سَعِيدٍ الْخُدْرِيِّ، قَالَ أَوَّلُ مَنْ أَسْرَجَ فِي الْمَسَاجِدِ تَمِيمٌ الدَّارِيُّ ‏.‏", "bengali": "", "english": "\"The first person who put lamps in the mosque was Tamim Ad-Dari.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "براء بن عازب رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم سے سوال کیا گیا: کیا اونٹ کا گوش", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "494", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated that Abu Sa'eed Al-Khudri said:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "495", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ عُثْمَانَ الْعُثْمَانِيُّ أَبُو مَرْوَانَ، حَدَّثَنَا إِبْرَاهِيمُ بْنُ سَعْدٍ، عَنِ ابْنِ شِهَابٍ، عَنْ حُمَيْدِ بْنِ عَبْدِ الرَّحْمَنِ بْنِ عَوْفٍ، عَنْ أَبِي هُرَيْرَةَ، وَأَبِي، سَعِيدٍ الْخُدْرِيِّ أَنَّهُمَا أَخْبَرَاهُ أَنَّ رَسُولَ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ رَأَى نُخَامَةً فِي جِدَارِ الْمَسْجِدِ فَتَنَاوَلَ حَصَاةً فَحَكَّهَا ثُمَّ قَالَ ‏ ‏ إِذَا تَنَخَّمَ أَحَدُكُمْ فَلاَ يَتَنَخَّمَنَّ قِبَلَ وَجْهِهِ وَلاَ عَنْ يَمِينِهِ وَلْيَبْزُقْ عَنْ شِمَالِهِ أَوْ تَحْتَ قَدَمِهِ الْيُسْرَى ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "The Messenger of Allah saw some sputum on the wall of the mosque. He picked up a stone and scraped it off, then he said, \"If anyone of you needs to spit, he should not spit in fro not of him or to his right; let him spit to his right; let him spit to his left or under his left foot.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "It is narrated from Abu Hurairah and Abu Sa'eed Al-Khudri that:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "496", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ طَرِيفٍ، حَدَّثَنَا عَائِذُ بْنُ حَبِيبٍ، عَنْ حُمَيْدٍ، عَنْ أَنَسٍ، أَنَّ النَّبِيَّ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ رَأَى نُخَامَةً فِي قِبْلَةِ الْمَسْجِدِ فَغَضِبَ حَتَّى احْمَرَّ وَجْهُهُ فَجَاءَتْهُ امْرَأَةٌ مِنَ الأَنْصَارِ فَحَكَّتْهَا وَجَعَلَتْ مَكَانَهَا خَلُوقًا فَقَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ ‏ ‏ مَا أَحْسَنَ هَذَا ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "The Prophet saw some sputum in the prayer direction of the mosque and he became so angry that his face turned red. Then a woman from among the Ansar came and scraped it off, and put some Khaluq on that spot. The Messenger of Allah said: \"How good this is.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated from Anas that:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "497", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ رُمْحٍ الْمِصْرِيُّ، أَنْبَأَنَا اللَّيْثُ بْنُ سَعْدٍ، عَنْ نَافِعٍ، عَنْ عَبْدِ اللَّهِ بْنِ عُمَرَ، قَالَ رَأَى رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ نُخَامَةً فِي قِبْلَةِ الْمَسْجِدِ وَهُوَ يُصَلِّي بَيْنَ يَدَىِ النَّاسِ فَحَتَّهَا ثُمَّ قَالَ حِينَ انْصَرَفَ مِنَ الصَّلاَةِ ‏ ‏ إِنَّ أَحَدَكُمْ إِذَا كَانَ فِي الصَّلاَةِ كَانَ اللَّهُ قِبَلَ وَجْهِهِ فَلاَ يَتَنَخَّمَنَّ أَحَدُكُمْ قِبَلَ وَجْهِهِ فِي الصَّلاَةِ ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "\"The Messenger of Allah saw some sputum in the prayer direction of the mosque, when he was praying in front of the people. He scratched it off, then when the prayer was over, he said: 'When anyone of you is performing prayer, Allah is before him, so none of you should spit toward the front while praying.'\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated that 'Abdullah bin 'Umar said:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "498", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا عَلِيُّ بْنُ مُحَمَّدٍ، حَدَّثَنَا وَكِيعٌ، عَنْ هِشَامِ بْنِ عُرْوَةَ، عَنْ أَبِيهِ، عَنْ عَائِشَةَ، أَنَّ النَّبِيَّ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ حَكَّ بُزَاقًا فِي قِبْلَةِ الْمَسْجِدِ ‏.‏", "bengali": "", "english": "The Prophet scratched some spittle from the prayer direction of the mosque.", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "عبداللہ بن عباس رضی اللہ عنہما سے روایت ہے کہ  نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  دودھ پی کر کل", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "498", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated from 'Aishah that:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "499", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا عَلِيُّ بْنُ مُحَمَّدٍ، حَدَّثَنَا وَكِيعٌ، عَنْ أَبِي سِنَانٍ، سَعِيدِ بْنِ سِنَانٍ عَنْ عَلْقَمَةَ بْنِ مَرْثَدٍ، عَنْ سُلَيْمَانَ بْنِ بُرَيْدَةَ، عَنْ أَبِيهِ، قَالَ صَلَّى رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ فَقَالَ رَجُلٌ مَنْ دَعَا إِلَى الْجَمَلِ الأَحْمَرِ فَقَالَ النَّبِيُّ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ ‏ ‏ لاَ وَجَدْتَهُ إِنَّمَا بُنِيَتِ الْمَسَاجِدُ لِمَا بُنِيَتْ لَهُ ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "\"The Messenger of Allah performed prayer, then a man said: 'Who was looking for the red camel?' The Prophet said: 'May you not find it! The mosques were built for that for which they were built.'\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated from Sulaiman bin Burdah that his father said:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "500", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ رُمْحٍ، أَنْبَأَنَا ابْنُ لَهِيعَةَ، ح وَحَدَّثَنَا أَبُو كُرَيْبٍ، حَدَّثَنَا حَاتِمُ بْنُ إِسْمَاعِيلَ، جَمِيعًا عَنِ ابْنِ عَجْلاَنَ، عَنْ عَمْرِو بْنِ شُعَيْبٍ، عَنْ أَبِيهِ، عَنْ جَدِّهِ، أَنَّ رَسُولَ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ نَهَى عَنْ إِنْشَادِ الضَّالَّةِ فِي الْمَسْجِدِ ‏.‏", "bengali": "", "english": "The Messenger of Allah forbade making lost-and-found announcements in the mosque.", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "سہل بن سعد ساعدی رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت ہے کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  دودھ پی کر کل", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "500", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated from 'Amr bin Shu'aib from his father, from his grandfather that:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "501", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا يَعْقُوبُ بْنُ حُمَيْدِ بْنِ كَاسِبٍ، حَدَّثَنَا عَبْدُ اللَّهِ بْنُ وَهْبٍ، أَخْبَرَنِي حَيْوَةُ بْنُ شُرَيْحٍ، عَنْ مُحَمَّدِ بْنِ عَبْدِ الرَّحْمَنِ الأَسَدِيِّ أَبِي الأَسْوَدِ، عَنْ أَبِي عَبْدِ اللَّهِ، مَوْلَى شَدَّادِ بْنِ الْهَادِ أَنَّهُ سَمِعَ أَبَا هُرَيْرَةَ، يَقُولُ سَمِعْتُ رَسُولَ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ يَقُولُ ‏ ‏ مَنْ سَمِعَ رَجُلاً يَنْشُدُ ضَالَّةً فِي الْمَسْجِدِ فَلْيَقُلْ لاَ رَدَّ اللَّهُ عَلَيْكَ فَإِنَّ الْمَسَاجِدَ لَمْ تُبْنَ لِهَذَا ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "He heard Abu Hurairah say: \"I heard the Messenger of Allah say: 'Whoever hears a man making a lost-and-found announcement in the mosque, let him say: \"May Allah not return it to you!\" For the mosques were not built for that.'\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated from Abu 'Abdullah, the freed slave of Shaddad bin Had that:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "502", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو بَكْرِ بْنُ أَبِي شَيْبَةَ، حَدَّثَنَا يَزِيدُ بْنُ هَارُونَ، ح وَحَدَّثَنَا أَبُو بِشْرٍ، بَكْرُ بْنُ خَلَفٍ حَدَّثَنَا يَزِيدُ بْنُ زُرَيْعٍ، قَالاَ حَدَّثَنَا هِشَامُ بْنُ حَسَّانَ، عَنْ مُحَمَّدِ بْنِ سِيرِينَ، عَنْ أَبِي هُرَيْرَةَ، قَالَ قَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ ‏ ‏ إِنْ لَمْ تَجِدُوا إِلاَّ مَرَابِضَ الْغَنَمِ وَأَعْطَانَ الإِبِلِ فَصَلُّوا فِي مَرَابِضِ الْغَنَمِ وَلاَ تُصَلُّوا فِي أَعْطَانِ الإِبِلِ ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "The Messenger of Allah said: \"If you cannot find anywhere (for prayer) except sheep's resting-places and camels' resting-places, then perform prayer in the sheep's resting-places and do not perform prayer in the camels' resting-places.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated that Abu Hurairah said:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "503", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو بَكْرِ بْنُ أَبِي شَيْبَةَ، حَدَّثَنَا هُشَيْمٌ، عَنْ يُونُسَ، عَنِ الْحَسَنِ، عَنْ عَبْدِ اللَّهِ بْنِ مُغَفَّلٍ الْمُزَنِيِّ، قَالَ قَالَ النَّبِيُّ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ ‏ ‏ صَلُّوا فِي مَرَابِضِ الْغَنَمِ وَلاَ تُصَلُّوا فِي أَعْطَانِ الإِبِلِ فَإِنَّهَا خُلِقَتْ مِنَ الشَّيَاطِينِ ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "\"The Prophet said: 'Perform prayer in the sheep's resting-places and do not perform prayer in the camels' resting-places, for they were created from the devils.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated that 'Abdullah bin Mughaffal Al-Muzani said:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "504", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو بَكْرِ بْنُ أَبِي شَيْبَةَ، حَدَّثَنَا زَيْدُ بْنُ الْحُبَابِ، حَدَّثَنَا عَبْدُ الْمَلِكِ بْنُ رَبِيعِ بْنِ سَبْرَةَ بْنِ مَعْبَدٍ الْجُهَنِيُّ، أَخْبَرَنِي أَبِي، عَنْ أَبِيهِ، أَنَّ رَسُولَ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ قَالَ ‏ ‏ لاَ يُصَلَّى فِي أَعْطَانِ الإِبِلِ وَيُصَلَّى فِي مُرَاحِ الْغَنَمِ ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "\"My father told me, from his father that the Messenger of Allah said: 'Do not perform prayer in the camels' resting-places, and perform prayer in the sheep's resting-places.'\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "'Abdul-Malik bin Rabi' bin Sabrah bin Ma'bad Al-Juhani said:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "505", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو بَكْرِ بْنُ أَبِي شَيْبَةَ، حَدَّثَنَا إِسْمَاعِيلُ بْنُ إِبْرَاهِيمَ، وَأَبُو مُعَاوِيَةَ عَنْ لَيْثٍ، عَنْ عَبْدِ اللَّهِ بْنِ الْحَسَنِ، عَنْ أُمِّهِ، عَنْ فَاطِمَةَ بِنْتِ رَسُولِ اللَّهِ، ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ قَالَتْ كَانَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ إِذَا دَخَلَ الْمَسْجِدَ يَقُولُ ‏\"‏ بِسْمِ اللَّهِ وَالسَّلاَمُ عَلَى رَسُولِ اللَّهِ اللَّهُمَّ اغْفِرْ لِي ذُنُوبِي وَافْتَحْ لِي أَبْوَابَ رَحْمَتِكَ ‏\"‏ ‏.‏ وَإِذَا خَرَجَ قَالَ ‏\"‏ بِسْمِ اللَّهِ وَالسَّلاَمُ عَلَى رَسُولِ اللَّهِ اللَّهُمَّ اغْفِرْ لِي ذُنُوبِي وَافْتَحْ لِي أَبْوَابَ فَضْلِكَ ‏\"‏ ‏.‏", "bengali": "", "english": "\"Whenever the Messenger of Allah entered the mosque he would say: 'Bismillah, was-salamu 'ala Rasulillah, Allahummagh-firli dhunubi waftah li abwaba rahmatika. (In the Name of Allah, and peace be upon the Messenger of Allah. O Allah, forgive me my sins and open to me the gates of Your mercy).' When he left he would say: 'Bismillah, was-salamu 'ala Rasulillah, Allahummagh-firli dhunubi waftah li abwaba fadlika. (In the Name of Allah, and peace be upon the Messenger of Allah. O Allah, forgive me my sins and open to me the gates of Your bounty).'\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "مقداد بن اسود رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  انہوں نے نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم سے اس شخص کے متعلق سوال", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "505", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated that Fatimah the daughter of the Messenger of Allah said:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "506", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا عَمْرُو بْنُ عُثْمَانَ بْنِ سَعِيدِ بْنِ كَثِيرِ بْنِ دِينَارٍ الْحِمْصِيُّ، وَعَبْدُ الْوَهَّابِ بْنُ الضَّحَّاكِ، قَالاَ حَدَّثَنَا إِسْمَاعِيلُ بْنُ عَيَّاشٍ، عَنْ عُمَارَةَ بْنِ غَزِيَّةَ، عَنْ رَبِيعَةَ بْنِ أَبِي عَبْدِ الرَّحْمَنِ، عَنْ عَبْدِ الْمَلِكِ بْنِ سَعِيدِ بْنِ سُوَيْدٍ الأَنْصَارِيِّ، عَنْ أَبِي حُمَيْدٍ السَّاعِدِيِّ، قَالَ قَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ ‏ ‏ إِذَا دَخَلَ أَحَدُكُمُ الْمَسْجِدَ فَلْيُسَلِّمْ عَلَى النَّبِيِّ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ ثُمَّ لْيَقُلِ اللَّهُمَّ افْتَحْ لِي أَبْوَابَ رَحْمَتِكَ ‏.‏ وَإِذَا خَرَجَ فَلْيَقُلِ اللَّهُمَّ إِنِّي أَسْأَلُكَ مِنْ فَضْلِكَ ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "\"The Messenger of Allah said: 'When anyone of you enters the mosque, let him send peace upon the prophet, then let him say: \"Allahummaftah li abwaba rahmatika (O Allah, open to me the gates of Your mercy).\" And when he leaves, let him say: \"Allahumma inni as'aluka min fadlika. (O Allah, I ask of you from Your bounty).\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated that Abu Humaid As-Sa'idi said:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "507", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ بَشَّارٍ، حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو بَكْرٍ الْحَنَفِيُّ، حَدَّثَنَا الضَّحَّاكُ بْنُ عُثْمَانَ، حَدَّثَنِي سَعِيدٌ الْمَقْبُرِيُّ، عَنْ أَبِي هُرَيْرَةَ، أَنَّ رَسُولَ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ قَالَ ‏ ‏ إِذَا دَخَلَ أَحَدُكُمُ الْمَسْجِدَ فَلْيُسَلِّمْ عَلَى النَّبِيِّ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ وَلْيَقُلِ اللَّهُمَّ افْتَحْ لِي أَبْوَابَ رَحْمَتِكَ وَإِذَا خَرَجَ فَلْيُسَلِّمْ عَلَى النَّبِيِّ وَلْيَقُلِ اللَّهُمَّ اعْصِمْنِي مِنَ الشَّيْطَانِ الرَّجِيمِ ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "The Mesenger of Allah said: \"When anyone of enters the mosque, let him send peace upon the Prophet, then let him say: 'Allahumma aftahli abwaba rahmatik (O Allah, open to me the gates of Your mercy).' And when he leaves, let him send peace upon the Prophet and say: 'Allahumma- simni minash-shaitanir-rajim (O Allah, protect me from the accursed Shaitan).'\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated from Abu Hurairah that:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "508", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو بَكْرِ بْنُ أَبِي شَيْبَةَ، حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو مُعَاوِيَةَ، عَنِ الأَعْمَشِ، عَنْ أَبِي صَالِحٍ، عَنْ أَبِي هُرَيْرَةَ، قَالَ قَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ ‏ ‏ إِذَا تَوَضَّأَ أَحَدُكُمْ فَأَحْسَنَ الْوُضُوءَ ثُمَّ أَتَى الْمَسْجِدَ لاَ يَنْهَزُهُ إِلاَّ الصَّلاَةُ لاَ يُرِيدُ إِلاَّ الصَّلاَةَ لَمْ يَخْطُ خَطْوَةً إِلاَّ رَفَعَهُ اللَّهُ بِهَا دَرَجَةً وَحَطَّ عَنْهُ بِهَا خَطِيئَةً حَتَّى يَدْخُلَ الْمَسْجِدَ فَإِذَا دَخَلَ الْمَسْجِدَ كَانَ فِي صَلاَةٍ مَا كَانَتِ الصَّلاَةُ تَحْبِسُهُ ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "\"The Messenger of Allah said: 'When one of you performs ablution and does it well, then he comes to the mosque with no other motive but prayer and not seeking anything other than the prayer, he does not take one step but Allah raises him in status one degree thereby, and takes away one of his sins, until he enters the mosque. When he enters the mosque he is in a state of prayer so long as he is waiting for the prayer.'\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated that Abu Hurairah said:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "509", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو مَرْوَانَ الْعُثْمَانِيُّ، مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ عُثْمَانَ حَدَّثَنَا إِبْرَاهِيمُ بْنُ سَعْدٍ، عَنِ ابْنِ شِهَابٍ، عَنْ سَعِيدِ بْنِ الْمُسَيَّبِ، وَأَبِي، سَلَمَةَ عَنْ أَبِي هُرَيْرَةَ، أَنَّ رَسُولَ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ قَالَ ‏ ‏ إِذَا أُقِيمَتِ الصَّلاَةُ فَلاَ تَأْتُوهَا وَأَنْتُمْ تَسْعَوْنَ وَأْتُوهَا تَمْشُونَ وَعَلَيْكُمُ السَّكِينَةُ فَمَا أَدْرَكْتُمْ فَصَلُّوا وَمَا فَاتَكُمْ فَأَتِمُّوا ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "The Messenger of Allah said: \"When the Iqamah is called for the prayer, do not come running. Come walking with tranquility. Whatever you catch up with, pray, and whatever you miss, complete it.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated from Abu Hurairah that:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "510", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو بَكْرِ بْنُ أَبِي شَيْبَةَ، حَدَّثَنَا يَحْيَى بْنُ أَبِي بُكَيْرٍ، حَدَّثَنَا زُهَيْرُ بْنُ مُحَمَّدٍ، عَنْ عَبْدِ اللَّهِ بْنِ مُحَمَّدِ بْنِ عَقِيلٍ، عَنْ سَعِيدِ بْنِ الْمُسَيَّبِ، عَنْ أَبِي سَعِيدٍ الْخُدْرِيِّ، أَنَّهُ سَمِعَ رَسُولَ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ يَقُولُ ‏\"‏ أَلاَ أَدُلُّكُمْ عَلَى مَا يُكَفِّرُ اللَّهُ بِهِ الْخَطَايَا وَيَزِيدُ بِهِ فِي الْحَسَنَاتِ ‏\"‏ ‏.‏ قَالُوا بَلَى يَا رَسُولَ اللَّهِ ‏.‏ قَالَ ‏\"‏ إِسْبَاغُ الْوُضُوءِ عِنْدَ الْمَكَارِهِ وَكَثْرَةُ الْخُطَى إِلَى الْمَسَاجِدِ وَانْتِظَارُ الصَّلاَةِ بَعْدَ الصَّلاَةِ ‏\"‏ ‏.‏", "bengali": "", "english": "He heard the Messenger of Allah say: 'Shall I not tell you of something by means of which Allah expiates for sins and increases good deeds?' They said: 'Yes, O Messenger of Allah.' He said: 'Performing ablution properly despite difficulties, increasing the number of steps one takes towards the mosque and waiting for the next prayer after prayer.'", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "بریدہ رضی اللہ عنہ فرماتے ہیں کہ  نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم ہر نماز کے لیے وضو کیا کرتے تھے، لیکن", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "510", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated from Abu Sa'eed Al-Khudri that :", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "511", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ بَشَّارٍ، حَدَّثَنَا مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ جَعْفَرٍ، حَدَّثَنَا شُعْبَةُ، عَنْ إِبْرَاهِيمَ الْهَجَرِيِّ، عَنْ أَبِي الأَحْوَصِ، عَنْ عَبْدِ اللَّهِ، قَالَ مَنْ سَرَّهُ أَنْ يَلْقَى اللَّهَ غَدًا مُسْلِمًا فَلْيُحَافِظْ عَلَى هَؤُلاَءِ الصَّلَوَاتِ الْخَمْسِ حَيْثُ يُنَادَى بِهِنَّ فَإِنَّهُنَّ مِنْ سُنَنِ الْهُدَى وَإِنَّ اللَّهَ شَرَعَ لِنَبِيِّكُمْ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ سُنَنَ الْهُدَى وَلَعَمْرِي لَوْ أَنَّ كُلَّكُمْ صَلَّى فِي بَيْتِهِ لَتَرَكْتُمْ سُنَّةَ نَبِيِّكُمْ وَلَوْ تَرَكْتُمْ سُنَّةَ نَبِيِّكُمْ لَضَلَلْتُمْ وَلَقَدْ رَأَيْتُنَا وَمَا يَتَخَلَّفُ عَنْهَا إِلاَّ مُنَافِقٌ مَعْلُومُ النِّفَاقِ وَلَقَدْ رَأَيْتُ الرَّجُلَ يُهَادَى بَيْنَ الرَّجُلَيْنِ حَتَّى يَدْخُلَ فِي الصَّفِّ وَمَا مِنْ رَجُلٍ يَتَطَهَّرُ فَيُحْسِنُ الطُّهُورَ فَيَعْمِدُ إِلَى الْمَسْجِدِ فَيُصَلِّي فِيهِ فَمَا يَخْطُو خَطْوَةً إِلاَّ رَفَعَ اللَّهُ لَهُ بِهَا دَرَجَةً وَحَطَّ عَنْهُ بِهَا خَطِيئَةً ‏.‏", "bengali": "", "english": "\"Whoever would like to meet Allah tomorrow (i.e. on the Day of Judgment) as a Muslim, let him preserve these five (daily) prayer when the call for them is given, for they are part of the ways of guidance, and Allah prescribed the ways of guidance to your Prophet. By Allah, if each of you prays in his house, you will have abandoned the Sunnah of your Prophet, and if you abandon the Sunnah of your Prophet you will go astray. I remember when no one stayed behind from the prayer except a hypocrite who was known for his hypocrisy. I have a man coming supported by two others, until he joined the row (of worshippers). There is no man who purifies himself and does it well, and comes to the mosque and prays there, but for every step that he takes, Allah raises him in status one degree thereby, and takes away one of his sins.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "فضل بن مبشر کہتے ہیں کہ  میں نے جابر بن عبداللہ رضی اللہ عنہما کو ایک ہی وضو سے کئی نماز پڑھتے دیکھا", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "511", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated that 'Abdullah said:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "512", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ سَعِيدِ بْنِ يَزِيدَ بْنِ إِبْرَاهِيمَ التُّسْتَرِيُّ، حَدَّثَنَا الْفَضْلُ بْنُ الْمُوَفَّقِ أَبُو الْجَهْمِ، حَدَّثَنَا فُضَيْلُ بْنُ مَرْزُوقٍ، عَنْ عَطِيَّةَ، عَنْ أَبِي سَعِيدٍ الْخُدْرِيِّ، قَالَ قَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ ‏ ‏ مَنْ خَرَجَ مِنْ بَيْتِهِ إِلَى الصَّلاَةِ فَقَالَ اللَّهُمَّ إِنِّي أَسْأَلُكَ بِحَقِّ السَّائِلِينَ عَلَيْكَ وَأَسْأَلُكَ بِحَقِّ مَمْشَاىَ هَذَا فَإِنِّي لَمْ أَخْرُجْ أَشَرًا وَلاَ بَطَرًا وَلاَ رِيَاءً وَلاَ سُمْعَةً وَخَرَجْتُ اتِّقَاءَ سُخْطِكَ وَابْتِغَاءَ مَرْضَاتِكَ فَأَسْأَلُكَ أَنْ تُعِيذَنِي مِنَ النَّارِ وَأَنْ تَغْفِرَ لِي ذُنُوبِي إِنَّهُ لاَ يَغْفِرُ الذُّنُوبَ إِلاَّ أَنْتَ - أَقْبَلَ اللَّهُ عَلَيْهِ بِوَجْهِهِ وَاسْتَغْفَرَ لَهُ سَبْعُونَ أَلْفَ مَلَكٍ ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "\"The Messenger of Allah said: 'Whoever leaves his house for the prayer and says: 'Allahumma inni asa'luka bi-haqqis-sa'ilina 'alaika, wa as'aluka bi-haqqi mamshaya hadha, fa inni lam akhruj asharan wa la batran, wa la riya'an, wa la sum'atan, wa kharajtu-ttiqa'a sukhtika wabtigha'a mardatika, fa as'aluka an tu'idhani minan-nari wa an taghfira li dhunubi, Innahu la yaghfirudh-dhunuba illa Anta. (O Allah, I ask You by the right that those who ask of You have over You, and I ask by virtue of this walking of mine, for I am not going out because of pride or vanity, or to show off or make a reputation, rather I am going out because I fear Your wrath and seek Your pleasure. So I ask You to protect me from the Fire and to forgive me my sins, for no one can forgive sins except You),' Allah will turn His Face towards him and seventy thousand angels will pray for his forgiveness.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated that Abu Sa'eed Al-Khudri said:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "513", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا رَاشِدُ بْنُ سَعِيدِ بْنِ رَاشِدٍ الرَّمْلِيُّ، حَدَّثَنَا الْوَلِيدُ بْنُ مُسْلِمٍ، عَنْ أَبِي رَافِعٍ، إِسْمَاعِيلَ بْنِ رَافِعٍ عَنْ سُمَىٍّ، مَوْلَى أَبِي بَكْرٍ عَنْ أَبِي صَالِحٍ، عَنْ أَبِي هُرَيْرَةَ، قَالَ قَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ ‏ ‏ الْمَشَّاءُونَ إِلَى الْمَسَاجِدِ فِي الظُّلَمِ أُولَئِكَ الْخَوَّاضُونَ فِي رَحْمَةِ اللَّهِ ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "\"The Messenger of Allah said: 'Those who walk to the mosque in the dark are those who are diving into the mercy of Allah.'\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated that Abu Hurairah said:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "514", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا إِبْرَاهِيمُ بْنُ مُحَمَّدٍ الْحَلَبِيُّ، حَدَّثَنَا يَحْيَى بْنُ الْحَارِثِ الشِّيرَازِيُّ، حَدَّثَنَا زُهَيْرُ بْنُ مُحَمَّدٍ التَّمِيمِيُّ، عَنْ أَبِي حَازِمٍ، عَنْ سَهْلِ بْنِ سَعْدٍ السَّاعِدِيِّ، قَالَ قَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ ‏ ‏ لِيَبْشَرِ الْمَشَّاءُونَ فِي الظُّلَمِ إِلَى الْمَسَاجِدِ بِنُورٍ تَامٍّ يَوْمَ الْقِيَامَةِ ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "\"The Messenger of Allah said: 'Give glad tidings, to those who walk to the mosques in the dark, of perfect light on the Day of Resurrection.'\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated that Sahl bin Sa'd As-Sa'idi said:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "515", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا مَجْزَأَةُ بْنُ سُفْيَانَ بْنِ أَسِيدٍ، مَوْلَى ثَابِتٍ الْبُنَانِيِّ حَدَّثَنَا سُلَيْمَانُ بْنُ دَاوُدَ الصَّائِغُ، عَنْ ثَابِتٍ الْبُنَانِيِّ، عَنْ أَنَسِ بْنِ مَالِكٍ، قَالَ قَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ ‏ ‏ بَشِّرِ الْمَشَّائِينَ فِي الظُّلَمِ إِلَى الْمَسَاجِدِ بِالنُّورِ التَّامِّ يَوْمَ الْقِيَامَةِ ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "\"The Messenger of Allah said: 'Give glad tidings to those who walk to the mosques in the dark, of perfect light on the Day of Resurrection.'\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated that Anas bin Malik said:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "516", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو بَكْرِ بْنُ أَبِي شَيْبَةَ، حَدَّثَنَا وَكِيعٌ، عَنِ ابْنِ أَبِي ذِئْبٍ، عَنْ عَبْدِ الرَّحْمَنِ بْنِ مِهْرَانَ، عَنْ عَبْدِ الرَّحْمَنِ بْنِ سَعْدٍ، عَنْ أَبِي هُرَيْرَةَ، قَالَ قَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ ‏ ‏ الأَبْعَدُ فَالأَبْعَدُ مِنَ الْمَسْجِدِ أَعْظَمُ أَجْرًا ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "\"The Messenger of Allah said: 'The greater the distance from the mosque, the greater the reward.'\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated that Abu Hurairah said:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "517", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا أَحْمَدُ بْنُ عَبْدَةَ، حَدَّثَنَا عَبَّادُ بْنُ عَبَّادٍ الْمُهَلَّبِيُّ، حَدَّثَنَا عَاصِمٌ الأَحْوَلُ، عَنْ أَبِي عُثْمَانَ النَّهْدِيِّ، عَنْ أُبَىِّ بْنِ كَعْبٍ، قَالَ كَانَ رَجُلٌ مِنَ الأَنْصَارِ بَيْتُهُ أَقْصَى بَيْتٍ بِالْمَدِينَةِ وَكَانَ لاَ تُخْطِئُهُ الصَّلاَةُ مَعَ رَسُولِ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ ‏.‏ قَالَ فَتَوَجَّعْتُ لَهُ فَقُلْتُ يَا فُلاَنُ لَوْ أَنَّكَ اشْتَرَيْتَ حِمَارًا يَقِيكَ الرَّمَضَ وَيَرْفَعُكَ مِنَ الْوَقَعِ وَيَقِيكَ هَوَامَّ الأَرْضِ ‏.‏ فَقَالَ وَاللَّهِ مَا أُحِبُّ أَنَّ بَيْتِي بِطُنُبِ بَيْتِ مُحَمَّدٍ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ ‏.‏ قَالَ فَحَمَلْتُ بِهِ حِمْلاً حَتَّى أَتَيْتُ بَيْتَ النَّبِيِّ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ فَذَكَرْتُ ذَلِكَ لَهُ فَدَعَاهُ فَسَأَلَهُ فَذَكَرَ لَهُ مِثْلَ ذَلِكَ وَذَكَرَ أَنَّهُ يَرْجُو فِي أَثَرِهِ فَقَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ ‏ ‏ إِنَّ لَكَ مَا احْتَسَبْتَ ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "\"There was a man among the Ansar whose house was the furthest house in Al-Madinah, yet he never missed prayer with the Messenger of Allah. I felt sorry for him and said: 'O so-and-so, why do you not buy a donkey to spare yourself the heat of the scorching sand, to carry over the stony ground, and to keep you away from the vermin on the ground?' He said: 'By Allah! I do not want to live so close to Muhammed.' This troubled me until I came to the house of the Prophet and mentioned that to him. He called (the man) and asked him, and he said something similar, and said that he was hoping for the reward for his steps. The Messenger of Allah said, 'You will have that (reward) that you sought.'\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated that Ubayy bin Ka'b said:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "518", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو مُوسَى، مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ الْمُثَنَّى حَدَّثَنَا خَالِدُ بْنُ الْحَارِثِ، حَدَّثَنَا حُمَيْدٌ، عَنْ أَنَسِ بْنِ مَالِكٍ، قَالَ أَرَادَتْ بَنُو سَلِمَةَ أَنْ يَتَحَوَّلُوا، مِنْ دِيَارِهِمْ إِلَى قُرْبِ الْمَسْجِدِ فَكَرِهَ النَّبِيُّ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ أَنْ يُعْرُوا الْمَدِينَةَ فَقَالَ ‏ ‏ يَا بَنِي سَلِمَةَ أَلاَ تَحْتَسِبُونَ آثَارَكُمْ ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏ فَأَقَامُوا ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "\"Banu Salimah wanted to move from their homes to somewhere near the mosque, but the Prophet did not want the outskirts of Al-madinah to be left vacant, so he said: 'O Banu Salimah, do you not hope for the reward of your footsteps?' So they stayed (where they were).\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated that Anas said:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "519", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا عَلِيُّ بْنُ مُحَمَّدٍ، حَدَّثَنَا وَكِيعٌ، حَدَّثَنَا إِسْرَائِيلُ، عَنْ سِمَاكٍ، عَنْ عِكْرِمَةَ، عَنِ ابْنِ عَبَّاسٍ، قَالَ كَانَتِ الأَنْصَارُ بَعِيدَةً مَنَازِلُهُمْ مِنَ الْمَسْجِدِ فَأَرَادُوا أَنْ يَقْتَرِبُوا فَنَزَلَتْ ‏{وَنَكْتُبُ مَا قَدَّمُوا وَآثَارَهُمْ}‏ قَالَ فَثَبَتُوا ‏.‏", "bengali": "", "english": "\"The houses of the Ansar were far from the mosque and they wanted to move closer. Then the following Verse was revealed: 'We record that which they send before (them), and their traces.'\"  He said: So they remained (where they were).\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "ابو سعید خدری رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم سے پوچھا گیا کہ مکہ اور مدینہ کے", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "519", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated that Ibn 'Abbas said:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "520", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو بَكْرِ بْنُ أَبِي شَيْبَةَ، حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو مُعَاوِيَةَ، عَنِ الأَعْمَشِ، عَنْ أَبِي صَالِحٍ، عَنْ أَبِي هُرَيْرَةَ، قَالَ قَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ ‏ ‏ صَلاَةُ الرَّجُلِ فِي جَمَاعَةٍ تَزِيدُ عَلَى صَلاَتِهِ فِي بَيْتِهِ وَصَلاَتِهِ فِي سُوقِهِ بِضْعًا وَعِشْرِينَ دَرَجَةً ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "\"The Messenger of Allah said: 'A man's prayer in congregation is twenty-some levels higher than his prayer in his house or in the marketplace.'\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated that Abu Hurairah said:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "521", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو مَرْوَانَ، مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ عُثْمَانَ الْعُثْمَانِيُّ حَدَّثَنَا إِبْرَاهِيمُ بْنُ سَعْدٍ، عَنِ ابْنِ شِهَابٍ، عَنْ سَعِيدِ بْنِ الْمُسَيَّبِ، عَنْ أَبِي هُرَيْرَةَ، أَنَّ رَسُولَ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ قَالَ ‏ ‏ فَضْلُ الْجَمَاعَةِ عَلَى صَلاَةِ أَحَدِكُمْ وَحْدَهُ خَمْسٌ وَعِشْرُونَ جُزْءًا ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "The Messenger of Allah said: \"The prayer in congregation is twenty-five times more virtuous than the prayer of anyone of you on his own.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated from Abu Hurairah that:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "522", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو كُرَيْبٍ، حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو مُعَاوِيَةَ، عَنْ هِلاَلِ بْنِ مَيْمُونٍ، عَنْ عَطَاءِ بْنِ يَزِيدَ، عَنْ أَبِي سَعِيدٍ الْخُدْرِيِّ، قَالَ قَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ ‏ ‏ صَلاَةُ الرَّجُلِ فِي جَمَاعَةٍ تَزِيدُ عَلَى صَلاَتِهِ فِي بَيْتِهِ خَمْسًا وَعِشْرِينَ دَرَجَةً ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "\"The Messenger of Allah said: 'the prayer of a man in congregation is twenty-five levels higher than his prayer in his home.'\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated that Abu Sa'eed Al-Khudri said:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "523", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا عَبْدُ الرَّحْمَنِ بْنُ عُمَرَ، رُسْتَهْ حَدَّثَنَا يَحْيَى بْنُ سَعِيدٍ، حَدَّثَنَا عُبَيْدُ اللَّهِ بْنُ عُمَرَ، عَنْ نَافِعٍ، عَنِ ابْنِ عُمَرَ، قَالَ قَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ ‏ ‏ صَلاَةُ الرَّجُلِ فِي جَمَاعَةٍ تَفْضُلُ عَلَى صَلاَةِ الرَّجُلِ وَحْدَهُ بِسَبْعٍ وَعِشْرِينَ دَرَجَةً ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "\"The Messenger of Allah said: 'The prayer of a man in congregation is twenty-seven levels more virtuous than a man's prayer on his own.'\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated that Ibn 'Umar said:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "524", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ مَعْمَرٍ، حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو بَكْرٍ الْحَنَفِيُّ، حَدَّثَنَا يُونُسُ بْنُ أَبِي إِسْحَاقَ، عَنْ أَبِيهِ، عَنْ عَبْدِ اللَّهِ بْنِ أَبِي بَصِيرٍ، عَنْ أَبِيهِ، عَنْ أُبَىِّ بْنِ كَعْبٍ، قَالَ قَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ ‏ ‏ صَلاَةُ الرَّجُلِ فِي جَمَاعَةٍ تَزِيدُ عَلَى صَلاَةِ الرَّجُلِ وَحْدَهُ أَرْبَعًا وَعِشْرِينَ أَوْ خَمْسًا وَعِشْرِينَ دَرَجَةً ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "\"The Messenger of Allah said: 'The prayer of a man in congregation is higher than his prayer on his own by twenty-four or twenty-five levels.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated that Ubayy bin Ka'b said:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "525", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو بَكْرِ بْنُ أَبِي شَيْبَةَ، حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو مُعَاوِيَةَ، عَنِ الأَعْمَشِ، عَنْ أَبِي صَالِحٍ، عَنْ أَبِي هُرَيْرَةَ، قَالَ قَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ ‏ ‏ لَقَدْ هَمَمْتُ أَنْ آمُرَ بِالصَّلاَةِ فَتُقَامَ ثُمَّ آمُرَ رَجُلاً فَيُصَلِّيَ بِالنَّاسِ ثُمَّ أَنْطَلِقَ بِرِجَالٍ مَعَهُمْ حُزَمٌ مِنْ حَطَبٍ إِلَى قَوْمٍ لاَ يَشْهَدُونَ الصَّلاَةَ فَأُحَرِّقَ عَلَيْهِمْ بُيُوتَهُمْ بِالنَّارِ ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "\"The Messenger of Allah said: 'I was thinking of commanding that the call to prayer be given, then I would tell a man to lead the people in prayer, then I would go out with some other men carrying bundles of wood, and go to people who do not attend the prayer, and burn their houses down around them.'\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated that Abu Hurairah said:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "526", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو بَكْرِ بْنُ أَبِي شَيْبَةَ، حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو أُسَامَةَ، عَنْ زَائِدَةَ، عَنْ عَاصِمٍ، عَنْ أَبِي رَزِينٍ، عَنِ ابْنِ أُمِّ مَكْتُومٍ، قَالَ قُلْتُ لِلنَّبِيِّ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ إِنِّي كَبِيرٌ ضَرِيرٌ شَاسِعُ الدَّارِ وَلَيْسَ لِي قَائِدٌ يُلاَوِمُنِي فَهَلْ تَجِدُ لِي مِنْ رُخْصَةٍ قَالَ ‏\"‏ هَلْ تَسْمَعُ النِّدَاءَ ‏\"‏ ‏.‏ قُلْتُ نَعَمْ ‏.‏ قَالَ ‏\"‏ مَا أَجِدُ لَكَ رُخْصَةً ‏\"‏ ‏.‏", "bengali": "", "english": "\"I said to the Prophet: 'I am an old man and blind; my house is far away, and I have no one to lead me. Is there any concession (for me not to have to attend the prayer in the mosque)?' He said: 'Can you hear the call?' I said: 'Yes.' He said: 'Then I do not find any concession for you.'\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "ابوسمح رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  میں نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کا خادم تھا، آپ کے پاس حسن یا حسین", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "526", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated that Ibn Umm Maktum said:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "527", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا عَبْدُ الْحَمِيدِ بْنُ بَيَانٍ الْوَاسِطِيُّ، أَنْبَأَنَا هُشَيْمٌ، عَنْ شُعْبَةَ، عَنْ عَدِيِّ بْنِ ثَابِتٍ، عَنْ سَعِيدِ بْنِ جُبَيْرٍ، عَنِ ابْنِ عَبَّاسٍ، عَنِ النَّبِيِّ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ قَالَ ‏ ‏ مَنْ سَمِعَ النِّدَاءَ فَلَمْ يَأْتِهِ فَلاَ صَلاَةَ لَهُ إِلاَّ مِنْ عُذْرٍ ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "The Prophet said: \"Whoever hears the call and does not come, his prayer is not valid, except for those who have an excuse.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated from Ibn 'Abbas that:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "528", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا عَلِيُّ بْنُ مُحَمَّدٍ، حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو أُسَامَةَ، عَنْ هِشَامٍ الدَّسْتَوَائِيِّ، عَنْ يَحْيَى بْنِ أَبِي كَثِيرٍ، عَنِ الْحَكَمِ بْنِ مِينَاءَ، أَخْبَرَنِي ابْنُ عَبَّاسٍ، وَابْنُ، عُمَرَ أَنَّهُمَا سَمِعَا النَّبِيَّ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ يَقُولُ عَلَى أَعْوَادِهِ ‏ ‏ لَيَنْتَهِيَنَّ أَقْوَامٌ عَنْ وَدْعِهِمُ الْجَمَاعَاتِ أَوْ لَيَخْتِمَنَّ اللَّهُ عَلَى قُلُوبِهِمْ ثُمَّ لَيَكُونُنَّ مِنَ الْغَافِلِينَ ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "They heard the Prophet say on his pulpit: \"People should desist from failing to attend the congregations, otherwise Allah will seal their hearts, and they will be among the negligent.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "Ibn 'Abbas and Ibn 'Umar narrated that:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "529", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا عُثْمَانُ بْنُ إِسْمَاعِيلَ الْهُذَلِيُّ الدِّمَشْقِيُّ، حَدَّثَنَا الْوَلِيدُ بْنُ مُسْلِمٍ، عَنِ ابْنِ أَبِي ذِئْبٍ، عَنِ الزِّبْرِقَانِ بْنِ عَمْرٍو الضَّمْرِيِّ، عَنْ أُسَامَةَ بْنِ زَيْدٍ، قَالَ قَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ ‏ ‏ لَيَنْتَهِيَنَّ رِجَالٌ عَنْ تَرْكِ الْجَمَاعَةِ أَوْ لأُحَرِّقَنَّ بُيُوتَهُمْ ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "\"The Messenger of Allah said: 'Let men desist from failing to attend the congregation, otherwise I will burn their houses down.'\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated that Usamah bin Zaid said:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "530", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا عَبْدُ الرَّحْمَنِ بْنُ إِبْرَاهِيمَ الدِّمَشْقِيُّ، حَدَّثَنَا الْوَلِيدُ بْنُ مُسْلِمٍ، حَدَّثَنَا الأَوْزَاعِيُّ، حَدَّثَنَا يَحْيَى بْنُ أَبِي كَثِيرٍ، حَدَّثَنِي مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ إِبْرَاهِيمَ التَّيْمِيُّ، حَدَّثَنِي عِيسَى بْنُ طَلْحَةَ، حَدَّثَتْنِي عَائِشَةُ، قَالَتْ قَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ ‏ ‏ لَوْ يَعْلَمُ النَّاسُ مَا فِي صَلاَةِ الْعِشَاءِ وَصَلاَةِ الْفَجْرِ لأَتَوْهُمَا وَلَوْ حَبْوًا ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "\"The Messenger of Allah said: 'If the people knew what (reward) there is in the 'Isha' prayer and fajr prayer, they would come even if they had to crawl.'\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "'Aishah said:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "531", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو بَكْرِ بْنُ أَبِي شَيْبَةَ، أَنْبَأَنَا أَبُو مُعَاوِيَةَ، عَنِ الأَعْمَشِ، عَنْ أَبِي صَالِحٍ، عَنْ أَبِي هُرَيْرَةَ، قَالَ قَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ ‏ ‏ إِنَّ أَثْقَلَ الصَّلاَةِ عَلَى الْمُنَافِقِينَ صَلاَةُ الْعِشَاءِ وَصَلاَةُ الْفَجْرِ وَلَوْ يَعْلَمُونَ مَا فِيهِمَا لأَتَوْهُمَا وَلَوْ حَبْوًا ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "\"The Messenger of Allah said: 'The most burdensome prayers for the hypocrites are the 'Isha' prayer and the Fajr prayer. If only they knew what (reward) there is in them, they would come to them even if they had to crawl.'\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated that Abu Hurairah said:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "532", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا عُثْمَانُ بْنُ أَبِي شَيْبَةَ، حَدَّثَنَا إِسْمَاعِيلُ بْنُ عَيَّاشٍ، عَنْ عُمَارَةَ بْنِ غَزِيَّةَ، عَنْ أَنَسِ بْنِ مَالِكٍ، عَنْ عُمَرَ بْنِ الْخَطَّابِ، عَنِ النَّبِيِّ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ أَنَّهُ كَانَ يَقُولُ ‏ ‏ مَنْ صَلَّى فِي مَسْجِدٍ جَمَاعَةً أَرْبَعِينَ لَيْلَةً لاَ تَفُوتُهُ الرَّكْعَةُ الأُولَى مِنْ صَلاَةِ الْعِشَاءِ كَتَبَ اللَّهُ لَهُ بِهَا عِتْقًا مِنَ النَّارِ ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "The Prophet used to say: \"Whoever performs prayer in congregation at the mosque for forty nights, never missing the first Rak'ah of the 'Isha' prayer, Allah will thereby decree for him salvation from the Fire.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated from 'Umar bin Khattab that:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "533", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو بَكْرِ بْنُ أَبِي شَيْبَةَ، حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو مُعَاوِيَةَ، عَنِ الأَعْمَشِ، عَنْ أَبِي صَالِحٍ، عَنْ أَبِي هُرَيْرَةَ، قَالَ قَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ ‏ ‏ إِنَّ أَحَدَكُمْ إِذَا دَخَلَ الْمَسْجِدَ كَانَ فِي صَلاَةٍ مَا كَانَتِ الصَّلاَةُ تَحْبِسُهُ وَالْمَلاَئِكَةُ يُصَلُّونَ عَلَى أَحَدِكُمْ مَادَامَ فِي مَجْلِسِهِ الَّذِي صَلَّى فِيهِ يَقُولُونَ اللَّهُمَّ اغْفِرْ لَهُ اللَّهُمَّ ارْحَمْهُ اللَّهُمَّ تُبْ عَلَيْهِ مَا لَمْ يُحْدِثْ فِيهِ مَا لَمْ يُؤْذِ فِيهِ ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "\"The Messenger of Allah said: 'When one of you enters the mosque, he is in a state of prayer, so long as the prayer keeps him there, and the angels will send prayer upon anyone of you so long as he remains in the place where he prayed, saying: \"O Allah, forgive him; O Allah, have mercy on him; O Allah, accept his repentance,\" so long as he does not commit Hadath nor disturb anyone.'\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated that Abu Hurairah said:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "534", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو بَكْرِ بْنُ أَبِي شَيْبَةَ، حَدَّثَنَا شَبَابَةُ، حَدَّثَنَا ابْنُ أَبِي ذِئْبٍ، عَنِ الْمَقْبُرِيِّ، عَنْ سَعِيدِ بْنِ يَسَارٍ، عَنْ أَبِي هُرَيْرَةَ، عَنِ النَّبِيِّ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ قَالَ ‏ ‏ مَا تَوَطَّنَ رَجُلٌ مُسْلِمٌ الْمَسَاجِدَ لِلصَّلاَةِ وَالذِّكْرِ إِلاَّ تَبَشْبَشَ اللَّهُ لَهُ كَمَا يَتَبَشْبَشُ أَهْلُ الْغَائِبِ بِغَائِبِهِمْ إِذَا قَدِمَ عَلَيْهِمْ ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "The Prophet said: \"A muslim does not regularly attend the mosques to perform prayer and remember Allah, but Allah feels happy with him just as the family of one who is absent feels happy when he comes back to them.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated from Abu Hurairah that:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "535", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا أَحْمَدُ بْنُ سَعِيدٍ الدَّارِمِيُّ، حَدَّثَنَا النَّضْرُ بْنُ شُمَيْلٍ، حَدَّثَنَا حَمَّادٌ، عَنْ ثَابِتٍ، عَنْ أَبِي أَيُّوبَ، عَنْ عَبْدِ اللَّهِ بْنِ عَمْرٍو، قَالَ صَلَّيْنَا مَعَ رَسُولِ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ الْمَغْرِبَ فَرَجَعَ مَنْ رَجَعَ وَعَقَّبَ مَنْ عَقَّبَ فَجَاءَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ مُسْرِعًا قَدْ حَفَزَهُ النَّفَسُ و قَدْ حَسَرَ عَنْ رُكْبَتَيْهِ فَقَالَ ‏ ‏ أَبْشِرُوا هَذَا رَبُّكُمْ قَدْ فَتَحَ بَابًا مِنْ أَبْوَابِ السَّمَاءِ يُبَاهِي بِكُمُ الْمَلاَئِكَةَ يَقُولُ انْظُرُوا إِلَى عِبَادِي قَدْ قَضَوْا فَرِيضَةً وَهُمْ يَنْتَظِرُونَ أُخْرَى ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "\"We performed the Maghrib (prayer) with the Messenger of Allah, then those who went back went back, and those who stayed, stayed. Then the Messenger of Allah came back in a hurry, out of breath, with his garment pulled up to his knees, and said: 'Be of good cheer, for your Lord has opened one of the gates of heaven and is boasting of you before the angels, saying: \"Look at My slaves; they have fulfilled one obligatory duty and are awaiting another.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated that 'Abdullah bin 'Amr said:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "536", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو كُرَيْبٍ، حَدَّثَنَا رِشْدِينُ بْنُ سَعْدٍ، عَنْ عَمْرِو بْنِ الْحَارِثِ، عَنْ دَرَّاجٍ، عَنْ أَبِي الْهَيْثَمِ، عَنْ أَبِي سَعِيدٍ، عَنْ رَسُولِ اللَّهِ ـ صلى الله عليه وسلم ـ قَالَ ‏\"‏ إِذَا رَأَيْتُمُ الرَّجُلَ يَعْتَادُ الْمَسَاجِدَ فَاشْهَدُوا لَهُ بِالإِيمَانِ قَالَ اللَّهُ تَعَالَى ‏{إِنَّمَا يَعْمُرُ مَسَاجِدَ اللَّهِ مَنْ آمَنَ بِاللَّهِ}‏ الآيَةَ ‏.‏", "bengali": "", "english": "The Messenger of Allah said: \"If you see a man frequenting the mosques, then bear witness to his faith. Allah says: 'The mosques of Allah shall be maintained only by those who believe in Allah and the Last Day. '\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "عمرو بن میمون کہتے ہیں کہ  میں نے سلیمان بن یسار سے سوال کیا: اگر کپڑے میں منی لگ جائے تو ہم صرف اتن", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "536", "narrator_chain": "It was narrated from Abu Sa'eed that:", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "735", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو بَكْرِ بْنُ أَبِي شَيْبَةَ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا يُونُسُ بْنُ مُحَمَّدٍ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَن", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated that 'Umar bin Khattab said:\"I heard the Messenger of Allah say: 'Whoever builds a mosque in which the Name of Allah is mentioned, Allah will build a house for him in Paradise", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "عمر بن خطاب رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  میں نے رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کو فرماتے ہوئے سنا:  جس شخ", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Daif'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 1", "international_number": "735", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "736", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ بَشَّارٍ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو بَكْرٍ الْحَنَفِيُّ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا عَب", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated that 'Uthman bin 'Affan said:\"I heard the Messenger of Allah say: 'Whoever builds a mosque for the sake of Allah, Allah will build something similar for him in Paradise", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "عثمان بن عفان رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  میں نے رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کو فرماتے ہوئے سنا:  جس", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Sahih Muslim'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 2", "international_number": "736", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "737", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا الْعَبَّاسُ بْنُ عُثْمَانَ الدِّمَشْقِيُّ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا الْوَلِيدُ بْنُ مُسْلِمٍ، ‏‏‏", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated that 'Ali bin Abu Talib said:\"The Messenger of Allah said: 'Whoever builds a mosque for the sake of Allah (from his own wealth), Allah will build a house for him in Paradise", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "علی بن ابی طالب رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  جس شخص نے اللہ تع", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Daif'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Daif'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Daif'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 3", "international_number": "737", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "738", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا يُونُسُ بْنُ عَبْدِ الْأَعْلَى، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا عَبْدُ اللَّهِ بْنُ وَهْبٍ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏عَنْ إ", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated from Jabir bin 'Abdullah that:The Messenger of Allah said: \"Whoever builds a mosque for the sake of Allah, like a sparrow's nest for Allah or even smaller, Allah will build for him a house in Paradise", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "جابر بن عبداللہ رضی اللہ عنہما کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  جس شخص نے پرندے", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Isnaad Sahih'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 4", "international_number": "738", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "739", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا عَبْدُ اللَّهِ بْنُ مُعَاوِيَةَ الْجُمَحِيُّ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا حَمَّادُ بْنُ سَلَمَةَ، ‏‏", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated that Anas bin Malik said:\"The Messenger of Allah said: 'The Hour will not begin until the people compete in (building) mosques", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "انس بن مالک رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  قیامت اس وقت قائم ہو", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Isnaad Sahih'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 5", "international_number": "739", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "740", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا جُبَارَةُ بْنُ الْمُغَلِّسِ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا عَبْدُ الْكَرِيمِ بْنُ عَبْدِ الرَّحْمَنِ ا", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated that Ibn 'Abbas said:The Messenger of Allah said: \"I see you building your mosque high after I am gone, just as the Jews built their synagogues high and the Christians built their churches high", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "عبداللہ بن عباس رضی اللہ عنہما کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  میرا خیال ہے کہ", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Daif'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Daif'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Daif'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Daif'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 6", "international_number": "740", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "741", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا جُبَارَةُ بْنُ الْمُغَلِّسِ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا عَبْدُ الْكَرِيمِ بْنُ عَبْدِ الرَّحْمَنِ،", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated that 'Umar bin Khattab said:The Messenger of Allah said: \"No people's deeds ever became evil deeds but they started to adorn their places of worship", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "عمر بن خطاب رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  جب کسی قوم کے اعمال خ", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Very Daif'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Very Daif'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Daif'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Daif'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 7", "international_number": "741", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "742", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا عَلِيُّ بْنُ مُحَمَّدٍ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا وَكِيعٌ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏عَنْ حَمَّادِ بْنِ سَلَمَةَ، ‏‏‏‏", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated that Anas bin Malik said:\"The location where the Prophet's Mosque was built belonged to Banu Najjar. In it there were date-palm trees and graves of the idolaters. The Prophet said to them: 'Name its price.' They said: 'We will never take any money for it.' The Prophet built it and they were assisting him, and the Prophet was saying: 'The real life is the life of the Hereafter so forgive the Ansar and the Muhajirah.' Before the mosque was built, the Prophet would perform prayer wherever he was when the time for prayer came", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "انس بن مالک رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  مسجد نبوی کی زمین قبیلہ بنو نجار کی ملکیت تھی، جس میں کھجور کے", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Sahih Muslim'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 8", "international_number": "742", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "743", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ يَحْيَى، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو هَمَّامٍ الدَّلَّالُ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا سَع", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated from 'Uthman bin Abul-'As that:The Messenger of Allah commanded him to build the mosque of Ta'if in the place where the Taghuts used to be", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "عثمان رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے انہیں حکم دیا کہ طائف میں مسجد وہیں", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Daif'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Daif'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Daif'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Daif'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 9", "international_number": "743", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "744", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ يَحْيَى، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا عَمْرُو بْنُ عُثْمَانَ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا مُوسَى", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated that Ibn 'Umar was asked about gardens in which excrement was thrown.:He said: \"If it has been watered several times, then perform prayer there,\" and he attributed that to the Prophet", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "عبداللہ بن عمر رضی اللہ عنہما سے روایت ہے کہ  ان سے ان باغات میں نماز پڑھنے کے متعلق پوچھا گیا جن می", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Daif'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Daif'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Daif'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Daif'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 10", "international_number": "744", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "745", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ يَحْيَى، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا يَزِيدُ بْنُ هَارُونَ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا سُفْيَان", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated that Abu Sa'eed Khudri said:\"The Messenger of Allah said: 'All the earth is a mosque, except for graveyards and Hammam", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "ابو سعید خدری رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  قبرستان اور حمام  (", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Isnaad Sahih'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 11", "international_number": "745", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "746", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ إِبْرَاهِيمَ الدِّمَشْقِيُّ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا عَبْدُ اللَّهِ بْنُ يَزِيدَ،", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated that Ibn 'Umar said:\"Allah's Messenger prohibited prayer from being performed in seven places: The garbage dump, the slaughtering area, the graveyard, the commonly used road, the bathroom, in the area that camels rest at, and above the Ka'bah", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "ابن عمر رضی اللہ عنہما کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے سات مقامات پر نماز پڑھنے سے منع", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Daif'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Daif'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Very Daif'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Daif'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 12", "international_number": "746", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "747", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا عَلِيُّ بْنُ دَاوُدَ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏ وَمُحَمَّدُ بْنُ أَبِي الْحُسَيْنِ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏قَالَا:‏‏‏‏ حَدَّث", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated from 'Umar bin Khattab that:The Messenger of Allah said: \"There are seven places where it is not permissible to perform the prayer: The top of the House of Allah; graveyards; garbage dumps; slaughterhouses; bathrooms; the area that camels rest, and the main road", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "عمر بن خطاب رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  سات مقامات پر نماز جا", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Daif'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Daif'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Daif'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Daif'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 13", "international_number": "747", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "748", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا يَحْيَى بْنُ عُثْمَانَ بْنِ سَعِيدِ بْنِ كَثِيرِ بْنِ دِينَارٍ الْحِمْصِيُّ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّث", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated from Ibn 'Umar that:The Messenger of Allah said: \"There are things which are not befitting for the mosque: it should not be taken as a thoroughfare; weapons should not be unsheathed in it; bows should not be drawn nor arrows shot in it; no one should pass through it carrying raw meat; no prescribed punishment or retaliatory punishment should be carried out in it; and it should not be used as a marketplace", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "عبداللہ بن عمر رضی اللہ عنہما کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  چند اعمال ایسے ہ", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Daif'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Daif'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Very Daif'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Daif'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 14", "international_number": "748", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "749", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا عَبْدُ اللَّهِ بْنُ سَعِيدٍ الْكِنْدِيُّ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو خَالِدٍ الْأَحْمَرُ، ‏‏‏", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated from 'Amr bin Shu'aib from his father that his grandfather said:\"The Messenger of Allah forbade buying and selling in the mosque, and reciting poetry in the mosque", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "عبداللہ بن عمرو بن العاص رضی اللہ عنہما کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے مسجد میں خرید و", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Hasan'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Hasan'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Hasan'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Isnaad Hasan'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 15", "international_number": "749", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "750", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا أَحْمَدُ بْنُ يُوسُفَ السُّلَمِيُّ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا مُسْلِمُ بْنُ إِبْرَاهِيمَ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَ", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated from Wathilah bin Asqa' that:The Prophet said: \"Keep your infants, your insane and your evil ones away from your mosques. Avoid engaging in transactions and disputes, raising your voices, carrying out your prescribed punishments and unsheathing your swords therein. Make places for purification at their gates, and perfume them with incense on Fridays.\" (Maudu)", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "واثلہ بن اسقع رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  تم اپنی مسجدوں کو بچ", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Daif'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Daif'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Very Daif'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Daif'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 16", "international_number": "750", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "751", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا إِسْحَاق بْنُ مَنْصُورٍ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا عَبْدُ اللَّهِ بْنُ نُمَيْرٍ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏أَنْبَأَنَا", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated that Ibn 'Umar said:\"We used to sleep in the mosque at the time of the Messenger of Allah", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "عبداللہ بن عمر رضی اللہ عنہما کہتے ہیں کہ  ہم رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کے زمانہ میں مسجد میں سوت", "grades": "{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Isnaad Sahih'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 17", "international_number": "751", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "752", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو بَكْرِ بْنُ أَبِي شَيْبَةَ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا الْحَسَنُ بْنُ مُوسَى، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَ", "bengali": "", "english": "Ya'ish bin Qais bin Tikhfah narrated that his father, who was one of the people of Suffah, said:\"The Messenger of Allah said to us: 'Come with me.' So we went to the house of 'Aishah, where we ate and drank. Then the Messenger of Allah said to us: 'If you want, you can sleep here, or if you want you can go out to the mosque.' We said: 'We will go out to the mosque", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "قیس بن طخفة (جو اصحاب صفہ میں سے تھے) کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے ہم سے فرمایا:  تم", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Daif'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Daif'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Daif'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Sahih'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 18", "international_number": "752", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "753", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا عَلِيُّ بْنُ مَيْمُونٍ الرَّقِّيُّ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ عُبَيْدٍ . ح وحَدَّثَ", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated that Abu Dharr Al-Ghifari said:\"I said: 'O Messenger of Allah! Which mosque was built first?' He said: 'Al-Masjid Al-Haram (in Makkah).' I said: 'Then which?' He said: 'then Al-Masjid Al-Aqsa (in Jerusalem).' I said: 'How many years between them?' He said: 'Forty years, but the whole earth is a mosque for you, so pray wherever you are when the time for prayer comes", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "ابوذر غفاری رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  میں نے پوچھا: اے اللہ کے رسول! سب سے پہلے کون سی مسجد بنائی گئ", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Sahih Muslim'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 19", "international_number": "753", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "754", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو مَرْوَانَ مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ عُثْمَانَ الْعُثْمَانِيُّ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا إِبْرَاهِيمُ ب", "bengali": "", "english": "Mahmud bin Rabi' Al-Ansari, who remembered that the Messenger of Allah spat a mouthful of water from a bucket into a well that belonged to them, narrated that :'Itban bin Malik As-Salimi who was the chief of his people Banu Salim and had participated in (the battle of) Badr with the Messenger of Allah said: \"I came to the Messenger of Allah and said: 'O Messenger of Allah, my sight is failing and the flood comes and prevents me from reaching the mosque of my people, and it is too hard for me to cross the water. Do you think you could come and perform prayer in my house in a place which I can then take as a place of prayer?' He said: 'I will do that.' The following day, the Messenger of Allah and Abu Bakr came, when the heat of the day had grown intense. He asked permission to enter, and I gave him permission. He did not sit down until he said: 'Where would you like me to perform prayer for you in your house?' I showed him the place where I wanted him to pray, so the Messenger of Allah stood and we lined up behind him, and he led us in praying two Rak'ah (units). Then I asked him to stay and eat some Khazirah that had been prepared for them", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "محمود بن ربیع انصاری رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت ہے  اور ان کو وہ کلی یاد تھی جو رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ و", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Sahih Muslim'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 20", "international_number": "754", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "755", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا يَحْيَى بْنُ الْفَضْلِ الْمُقْرِي، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو عَامِرٍ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا حَمَّ", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated from Abu Hurairah that:A man among the Ansar sent word to the Messenger of Allah saying: \"Come and designate a place in my house where I can perform prayer,' that was after he had become blind. So he went and did that", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "ابوہریرہ رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت ہے کہ  قبیلہ انصار کے ایک آدمی نے نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کے پاس", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Hasan'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Isnaad Hasan'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 21", "international_number": "755", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "756", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا يَحْيَى بْنُ حَكِيمٍ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا ابْنُ أَبِي عَدِيٍّ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏عَنْ ابْنِ عَوْنٍ، ‏‏‏‏", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated that Anas bin Malik said:\"One of my paternal uncles made some food for the Prophet and said to the Prophet: 'I would like you to eat and perform prayer in my house.' So he went to him, and in his house there was one of these Fahl. He ordered that a corner be swept and water sprinkled in it, then he performed prayer and we prayed with him.'\" (Sahih)Abu 'Abdullah bin Majah said: A Fahl is a mat that has become black (through use)", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "انس بن مالک رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  میرے ایک چچا نے نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کے لیے کھانا تیار", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Isnaad Sahih'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 22", "international_number": "756", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "757", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا هِشَامُ بْنُ عَمَّارٍ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا عَبْدُ الرَّحْمَنِ بْنُ سُلَيْمَانَ بْنِ أَبِي ال", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated that Abu Sa'eed Al-Khudri said:\"The Messenger of Allah said: 'Whoever removes something harmful from the mosque, Allah will build for him a house in Paradise", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "ابو سعید خدری رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  جو شخص مسجد سے کوڑا", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Daif'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Daif'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Daif'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Daif'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 23", "international_number": "757", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "758", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا عَبْدُ الرَّحْمَنِ بْنُ بِشْرِ بْنِ الْحَكَمِ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏ وَأَحْمَدُ بْنُ الْأَزْهَرِ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated from 'Aishah that:The Messenger of Allah commanded that mosque to be built in (Ad-Dur) villages, and that they be purified and perfumed", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "ام المؤمنین عائشہ رضی اللہ عنہا سے روایت ہے کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے حکم فرمایا کہ  محلوں", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Isnaad Sahih'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 24", "international_number": "758", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "759", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا رِزْقُ اللَّهِ بْنُ مُوسَى، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا يَعْقُوبُ بْنُ إِسْحَاق الْحَضْرَمِيُّ، ‏‏‏‏", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated from 'Aishah that:The Messenger of Allah commanded that places of prayer be established in villages, and that they be purified and perfumed", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "ام المؤمنین عائشہ رضی اللہ عنہا کہتی ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے حکم فرمایا:  محلوں میں", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Sahih'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 25", "international_number": "759", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "760", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا أَحْمَدُ بْنُ سِنَانٍ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو مُعَاوِيَةَ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏عَنْ خَالِدِ بْنِ إِيَاس", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated that Abu Sa'eed Al-Khudri said:\"The first person who put lamps in the mosque was Tamim Ad-Dari", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "ابو سعید خدری رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  سب سے پہلے تمیم داری رضی اللہ عنہ نے مسجدوں میں چراغ جلایا ت", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Very Daif'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Very Daif'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Very Daif'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Daif'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 26", "international_number": "760", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "761", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ عُثْمَانَ الْعُثْمَانِيُّ أَبُو مَرْوَانَ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا إِبْرَاهِيمُ ب", "bengali": "", "english": "It is narrated from Abu Hurairah and Abu Sa'eed Al-Khudri that:The Messenger of Allah saw some sputum on the wall of the mosque. He picked up a stone and scraped it off, then he said, \"If anyone of you needs to spit, he should not spit in fro not of him or to his right; let him spit to his right; let him spit to his left or under his left foot", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "ابوہریرہ اور ابو سعید خدری رضی اللہ عنہما کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے مسجد کی دیوار", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Sahih Muslim'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 27", "international_number": "761", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "762", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ طَرِيفٍ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا عَائِذُ بْنُ حَبِيبٍ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏عَنْ حُمَيْدٍ، ‏‏‏‏‏", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated from Anas that:The Prophet saw some sputum in the prayer direction of the mosque and he became so angry that his face turned red. Then a woman from among the Ansar came and scraped it off, and put some Khaluq on that spot. The Messenger of Allah said: \"How good this is", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "انس رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت ہے کہ  نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے مسجد کی دیوار قبلہ پر بلغم دیکھا، تو", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Isnaad Sahih'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 28", "international_number": "762", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "763", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ رُمْحٍ الْمِصْرِيُّ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏أَنْبَأَنَا اللَّيْثُ بْنُ سَعْدٍ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏عَنْ ن", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated that 'Abdullah bin 'Umar said:\"The Messenger of Allah saw some sputum in the prayer direction of the mosque, when he was praying in front of the people. He scratched it off, then when the prayer was over, he said: 'When anyone of you is performing prayer, Allah is before him, so none of you should spit toward the front while praying", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "عبداللہ بن عمر رضی اللہ عنہما کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے مسجد کی دیوار قبلہ پر بلغ", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Sahih - Bukhari And Muslim'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 29", "international_number": "763", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "764", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا عَلِيُّ بْنُ مُحَمَّدٍ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا وَكِيعٌ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏عَنْ هِشَامِ بْنِ عُرْوَةَ، ‏‏‏‏‏", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated from 'Aishah that:The Prophet scratched some spittle from the prayer direction of the mosque", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "ام المؤمنین عائشہ رضی اللہ عنہا کہتی ہیں کہ  نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے مسجد کے قبلہ کی دیوار پر", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Isnaad Sahih'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 30", "international_number": "764", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "765", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا عَلِيُّ بْنُ مُحَمَّدٍ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا وَكِيعٌ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏عَنْ أَبِي سِنَانٍ سَعِيدِ بْنِ س", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated from Sulaiman bin Burdah that his father said:\"The Messenger of Allah performed prayer, then a man said: 'Who was looking for the red camel?' The Prophet said: 'May you not find it! The mosques were built for that for which they were built", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "بریدہ رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے نماز پڑھائی، تو ایک شخص نے کہا: میرا", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Sahih Muslim'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 31", "international_number": "765", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "766", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ رُمْحٍ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏أَنْبَأَنَا عَبْدُ اللَّهِ بْنُ لَهِيعَةَ . ح وحَدَّثَنَا أَ", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated from 'Amr bin Shu'aib from his father, from his grandfather that:The Messenger of Allah forbade making lost-and-found announcements in the mosque", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "عبداللہ بن عمرو بن العاص رضی اللہ عنہما سے روایت ہے کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے مسجد میں گمش", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Hasan'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Hasan'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Hasan'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Hasan'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 32", "international_number": "766", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "767", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا يَعْقُوبُ بْنُ حُمَيْدِ بْنِ كَاسِبٍ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا عَبْدُ اللَّهِ بْنُ وَهْبٍ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated from Abu 'Abdullah, the freed slave of Shaddad bin Had that:He heard Abu Hurairah say: \"I heard the Messenger of Allah say: 'Whoever hears a man making a lost-and-found announcement in the mosque, let him say: \"May Allah not return it to you!\" For the mosques were not built for that", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "ابوہریرہ رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  میں نے رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کو فرماتے سنا:  جو شخص کسی کو", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Sahih Muslim'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 33", "international_number": "767", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "768", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو بَكْرِ بْنُ أَبِي شَيْبَةَ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا يَزِيدُ بْنُ هَارُونَ . ح وحَدَّثَنَا", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated that Abu Hurairah said:The Messenger of Allah said: \"If you cannot find anywhere (for prayer) except sheep's resting-places and camels' resting-places, then perform prayer in the sheep's resting-places and do not perform prayer in the camels' resting-places", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "ابوہریرہ رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  اگر تمہیں بکریوں اور اون", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Hasan'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 34", "international_number": "768", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "769", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو بَكْرِ بْنُ أَبِي شَيْبَةَ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا هُشَيْمٌ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏عَنْ يُونُسَ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏عَ", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated that 'Abdullah bin Mughaffal Al-Muzani said:\"The Prophet said: 'Perform prayer in the sheep's resting-places and do not perform prayer in the camels' resting-places, for they were created from the devils", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "عبداللہ بن مغفل مزنی رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  بکریوں کے با", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Hasan'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Hasan'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 35", "international_number": "769", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "770", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو بَكْرِ بْنُ أَبِي شَيْبَةَ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا زَيْدُ بْنُ الْحُبَابِ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَن", "bengali": "", "english": "Abdul-Malik bin Rabi' bin Sabrah bin Ma'bad Al-Juhani said:\"My father told me, from his father that the Messenger of Allah said: 'Do not perform prayer in the camels' resting-places, and perform prayer in the sheep's resting-places", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "معبد جہنی رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت ہے کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  اونٹ کے باڑے میں نما", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Hasan Sahih'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Hasan Sahih'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Sahih Lighairihi'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Isnaad Sahih'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 36", "international_number": "770", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "771", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو بَكْرِ بْنُ أَبِي شَيْبَةَ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا إِسْمَاعِيل بْنُ إِبْرَاهِيمَ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated that Fatimah the daughter of the Messenger of Allah said:\"Whenever the Messenger of Allah entered the mosque he would say: 'Bismillah, was-salamu 'ala Rasulillah, Allahummagh-firli dhunubi waftah li abwaba rahmatika. (In the Name of Allah, and peace be upon the Messenger of Allah. O Allah, forgive me my sins and open to me the gates of Your mercy).' When he left he would say: 'Bismillah, was-salamu 'ala Rasulillah, Allahummagh-firli dhunubi waftah li abwaba fadlika. (In the Name of Allah, and peace be upon the Messenger of Allah. O Allah, forgive me my sins and open to me the gates of Your bounty)", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کی صاحبزادی فاطمہ رضی اللہ عنہا کہتی ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وس", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Sahih Lighairihi'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Daif'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 37", "international_number": "771", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "772", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا عَمْرُو بْنُ عُثْمَانَ بْنِ سَعِيدِ بْنِ كَثِيرِ بْنِ دِينَارٍ الْحِمْصِيُّ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏ وَعَب", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated that Abu Humaid As-Sa'idi said:\"The Messenger of Allah said: 'When anyone of you enters the mosque, let him send peace upon the prophet, then let him say: \"Allahummaftah li abwaba rahmatika (O Allah, open to me the gates of Your mercy).\" And when he leaves, let him say: \"Allahumma inni as'aluka min fadlika. (O Allah, I ask of you from Your bounty)", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "ابو حمید ساعدی رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  جب کوئی شخص مسجد م", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Sahih Muslim'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 38", "international_number": "772", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "773", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ بَشَّارٍ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو بَكْرٍ الْحَنَفِيُّ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا الض", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated from Abu Hurairah that:The Mesenger of Allah said: \"When anyone of enters the mosque, let him send peace upon the Prophet, then let him say: 'Allahumma aftahli abwaba rahmatik (O Allah, open to me the gates of Your mercy).' And when he leaves, let him send peace upon the Prophet and say: 'Allahumma- simni minash-shaitanir-rajim (O Allah, protect me from the accursed Shaitan)", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "ابوہریرہ رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت ہے کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  جب کوئی شخص مسجد میں", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Sahih'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 39", "international_number": "773", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "774", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو بَكْرِ بْنُ أَبِي شَيْبَةَ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو مُعَاوِيَةَ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏عَنْ الْأَعْم", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated that Abu Hurairah said:\"The Messenger of Allah said: 'When one of you performs ablution and does it well, then he comes to the mosque with no other motive but prayer and not seeking anything other than the prayer, he does not take one step but Allah raises him in status one degree thereby, and takes away one of his sins, until he enters the mosque. When he enters the mosque he is in a state of prayer so long as he is waiting for the prayer", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "ابوہریرہ رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  جب کوئی شخص اچھی طرح وضو", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Sahih'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 40", "international_number": "774", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "775", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو مَرْوَانَ الْعُثْمَانِيُّ مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ عُثْمَانَ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا إِبْرَاهِيمُ ب", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated from Abu Hurairah that:The Messenger of Allah said: \"When the Iqamah is called for the prayer, do not come running. Come walking with tranquility. Whatever you catch up with, pray, and whatever you miss, complete it", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "ابوہریرہ رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت ہے کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  جب نماز کے لیے اقامت", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Sahih Muslim'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 41", "international_number": "775", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "776", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو بَكْرِ بْنُ أَبِي شَيْبَةَ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا يَحْيَى بْنُ أَبِي بُكَيْرٍ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَد", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated from Abu Sa'eed Al-Khudri that :He heard the Messenger of Allah say: 'Shall I not tell you of something by means of which Allah expiates for sins and increases good deeds?' They said: 'Yes, O Messenger of Allah.' He said: 'Performing ablution properly despite difficulties, increasing the number of steps one takes towards the mosque and waiting for the next prayer after prayer", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "ابو سعید خدری رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  انہوں نے رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کو فرماتے ہوئے سنا:  ک", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Hasan Sahih'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Hasan Sahih'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Hasan'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Hasan'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 42", "international_number": "776", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "777", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ بَشَّارٍ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ جَعْفَرٍ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا شُعْب", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated that 'Abdullah said:\"Whoever would like to meet Allah tomorrow (i.e. on the Day of Judgment) as a Muslim, let him preserve these five (daily) prayer when the call for them is given, for they are part of the ways of guidance, and Allah prescribed the ways of guidance to your Prophet. By Allah, if each of you prays in his house, you will have abandoned the Sunnah of your Prophet, and if you abandon the Sunnah of your Prophet you will go astray. I remember when no one stayed behind from the prayer except a hypocrite who was known for his hypocrisy. I have a man coming supported by two others, until he joined the row (of worshippers). There is no man who purifies himself and does it well, and comes to the mosque and prays there, but for every step that he takes, Allah raises him in status one degree thereby, and takes away one of his sins", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "عبداللہ بن مسعود رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  جس شخص کو خوشی ہ", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Hasan'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 43", "international_number": "777", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "778", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ سَعِيدِ بْنِ يَزِيدَ بْنِ إِبْرَاهِيمَ التُّسْتَرِيُّ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا ال", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated that Abu Sa'eed Al-Khudri said:\"The Messenger of Allah said: 'Whoever leaves his house for the prayer and says: 'Allahumma inni asa'luka bi-haqqis-sa'ilina 'alaika, wa as'aluka bi-haqqi mamshaya hadha, fa inni lam akhruj asharan wa la batran, wa la riya'an, wa la sum'atan, wa kharajtu-ttiqa'a sukhtika wabtigha'a mardatika, fa as'aluka an tu'idhani minan-nari wa an taghfira li dhunubi, Innahu la yaghfirudh-dhunuba illa Anta. (O Allah, I ask You by the right that those who ask of You have over You, and I ask by virtue of this walking of mine, for I am not going out because of pride or vanity, or to show off or make a reputation, rather I am going out because I fear Your wrath and seek Your pleasure. So I ask You to protect me from the Fire and to forgive me my sins, for no one can forgive sins except You),' Allah will turn His Face towards him and seventy thousand angels will pray for his forgiveness", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "ابو سعید خدری رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  جو شخص اپنے گھر سے", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Daif'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Daif'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Daif'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 44", "international_number": "778", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "779", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا رَاشِدُ بْنُ سَعِيدِ بْنِ رَاشِدٍ الرَّمْلِيُّ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا الْوَلِيدُ بْنُ مُسْلِمٍ", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated that Abu Hurairah said:\"The Messenger of Allah said: 'Those who walk to the mosque in the dark are those who are diving into the mercy of Allah", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "ابوہریرہ رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  تاریکیوں میں مسجدوں کی ج", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Daif'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Daif'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Daif'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 45", "international_number": "779", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "780", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا إِبْرَاهِيمُ بْنُ مُحَمَّدٍ الْحُلَبِيُّ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا يَحْيَى بْنُ الْحَارِثِ الشِّي", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated that Sahl bin Sa'd As-Sa'idi said:\"The Messenger of Allah said: 'Give glad tidings, to those who walk to the mosques in the dark, of perfect light on the Day of Resurrection", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "سہل بن سعد ساعدی رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  تاریکیوں میں  (", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Hasan'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Isnaad Hasan'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 46", "international_number": "780", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "781", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا مَجْزَأَةُ بْنُ سُفْيَانَ بْنِ أَسِيدٍ مَوْلَى ثَابِتٍ الْبُنَانِيِّ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا سُ", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated that Anas bin Malik said:\"The Messenger of Allah said: 'Give glad tidings to those who walk to the mosques in the dark, of perfect light on the Day of Resurrection", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "انس بن مالک رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  تاریکیوں میں مسجدوں ک", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Hasan Lighairihi'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Hasan'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 47", "international_number": "781", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "782", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو بَكْرِ بْنُ أَبِي شَيْبَةَ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا وَكِيعٌ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏عَنْ ابْنِ أَبِي ذِئْبٍ", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated that Abu Hurairah said:\"The Messenger of Allah said: 'The greater the distance from the mosque, the greater the reward", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "ابوہریرہ رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  مسجد میں جو جتنا ہی دور", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Sahih Lighairihi'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Isnaad Hasan'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 48", "international_number": "782", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "783", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا أَحْمَدُ بْنُ عَبْدَةَ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا عَبَّادُ بْنُ عَبَّادٍ الْمُهَلَّبِيُّ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَ", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated that Ubayy bin Ka'b said:\"There was a man among the Ansar whose house was the furthest house in Al-Madinah, yet he never missed prayer with the Messenger of Allah. I felt sorry for him and said: 'O so-and-so, why do you not buy a donkey to spare yourself the heat of the scorching sand, to carry over the stony ground, and to keep you away from the vermin on the ground?' He said: 'By Allah! I do not want to live so close to Muhammed.' This troubled me until I came to the house of the Prophet and mentioned that to him. He called (the man) and asked him, and he said something similar, and said that he was hoping for the reward for his steps. The Messenger of Allah said, 'You will have that (reward) that you sought", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "ابی بن کعب رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  مدینہ میں ایک انصاری شخص کا مکان انتہائی دوری پر تھا، اس کے باو", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Sahih Muslim'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 49", "international_number": "783", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "784", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو مُوسَى مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ الْمُثَنَّى، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا خَالِدُ بْنُ الْحَارِثِ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated that Anas said:\"Banu Salimah wanted to move from their homes to somewhere near the mosque, but the Prophet did not want the outskirts of Al-madinah to be left vacant, so he said: 'O Banu Salimah, do you not hope for the reward of your footsteps?' So they stayed (where they were)", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "انس بن مالک رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  بنو سلمہ نے ارادہ کیا کہ وہ اپنے پرانے گھروں کو جو مسجد نبوی س", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Sahih Bukhari'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 50", "international_number": "784", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "785", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا عَلِيُّ بْنُ مُحَمَّدٍ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا وَكِيعٌ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا إِسْرَائِيلُ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏عَ", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated that Ibn 'Abbas said:\"The houses of the Ansar were far from the mosque and they wanted to move closer. Then the following Verse was revealed: 'We record that which they send before (them), and their traces.'\" [Ya-Sin: 12] He said: So they remained (where they were)", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "عبداللہ بن عباس رضی اللہ عنہما کہتے ہیں کہ  انصار کے مکانات مسجد نبوی سے کافی دور تھے، ان لوگوں نے ا", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Sahih Lighairihi'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Daif'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 51", "international_number": "785", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "786", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو بَكْرِ بْنُ أَبِي شَيْبَةَ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو مُعَاوِيَةَ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏عَنْ الْأَعْم", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated that Abu Hurairah said:\"The Messenger of Allah said: 'A man's prayer in congregation is twenty-some levels higher than his prayer in his house or in the marketplace", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "ابوہریرہ رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  آدمی کا جماعت کے ساتھ ن", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Sahih - Bukhari And Muslim'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 52", "international_number": "786", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "787", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو مَرْوَانَ مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ عُثْمَانَ الْعُثْمَانِيُّ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا إِبْرَاهِيمُ ب", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated from Abu Hurairah that:The Messenger of Allah said: \"The prayer in congregation is twenty-five times more virtuous than the prayer of anyone of you on his own", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "ابوہریرہ رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت ہے کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  جماعت کی فضیلت تم میں", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Sahih - Bukhari And Muslim'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 53", "international_number": "787", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "788", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو كُرَيْبٍ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو مُعَاوِيَةَ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏عَنْ هِلَالِ بْنِ مَيْمُونٍ، ‏‏", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated that Abu Sa'eed Al-Khudri said:\"The Messenger of Allah said: 'the prayer of a man in congregation is twenty-five levels higher than his prayer in his home", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "ابو سعید خدری رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  آدمی کا جماعت کے س", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Sahih'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 54", "international_number": "788", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "789", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا عَبْدُ الرَّحْمَنِ بْنُ عُمَرَ رُسْتَةُ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا يَحْيَى بْنُ سَعِيدٍ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَد", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated that Ibn 'Umar said:\"The Messenger of Allah said: 'The prayer of a man in congregation is twenty-seven levels more virtuous than a man's prayer on his own", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "عبداللہ بن عمر رضی اللہ عنہما کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  آدمی کا جماعت ک", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Sahih Muslim'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 55", "international_number": "789", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "790", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا مُحَمَّدُ بْنُ مَعْمَرٍ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو بَكْرٍ الْحَنَفِيُّ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا يُو", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated that Ubayy bin Ka'b said:\"The Messenger of Allah said: 'The prayer of a man in congregation is higher than his prayer on his own by twenty-four or twenty-five levels", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "ابی بن کعب رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  آدمی کا جماعت کی نماز", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Hasan'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 56", "international_number": "790", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "791", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو بَكْرِ بْنُ أَبِي شَيْبَةَ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو مُعَاوِيَةَ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏عَنْ الْأَعْم", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated that Abu Hurairah said:\"The Messenger of Allah said: 'I was thinking of commanding that the call to prayer be given, then I would tell a man to lead the people in prayer, then I would go out with some other men carrying bundles of wood, and go to people who do not attend the prayer, and burn their houses down around them", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "ابوہریرہ رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  میرا پختہ ارادہ ہوا کہ ن", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Sahih'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 57", "international_number": "791", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "792", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو بَكْرِ بْنُ أَبِي شَيْبَةَ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو أُسَامَةَ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏عَنْ زَائِدَةَ،", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated that Ibn Umm Maktum said:\"I said to the Prophet: 'I am an old man and blind; my house is far away, and I have no one to lead me. Is there any concession (for me not to have to attend the prayer in the mosque)?' He said: 'Can you hear the call?' I said: 'Yes.' He said: 'Then I do not find any concession for you", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "عبداللہ ابن ام مکتوم رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  میں نے نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم سے کہا: میں بوڑھا", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Daif'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Daif'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 58", "international_number": "792", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "793", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا عَبْدُ الْحَمِيدِ بْنُ بَيَانٍ الْوَاسِطِيُّ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏أَنْبَأَنَا هُشَيْمٌ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏عَنْ شُعْ", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated from Ibn 'Abbas that:The Prophet said: \"Whoever hears the call and does not come, his prayer is not valid, except for those who have an excuse", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "عبداللہ بن عباس رضی اللہ عنہما کہتے ہیں کہ  نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  جس شخص نے اذان س", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Sahih'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 59", "international_number": "793", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "794", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا عَلِيُّ بْنُ مُحَمَّدٍ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو أُسَامَةَ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏عَنْ هِشَامٍ الدَّسْتُوَا", "bengali": "", "english": "Ibn 'Abbas and Ibn 'Umar narrated that:They heard the Prophet say on his pulpit: \"People should desist from failing to attend the congregations, otherwise Allah will seal their hearts, and they will be among the negligent", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "عبداللہ بن عباس اور عبداللہ بن عمر رضی اللہ عنہم خبر دیتے ہیں کہ  ان دونوں نے نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Sahih Muslim'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 60", "international_number": "794", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "795", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا عُثْمَانُ بْنُ إِسْمَاعِيل الْهُذَلِيُّ الدِّمَشْقِيُّ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا الْوَلِيدُ بْنُ", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated that Usamah bin Zaid said:\"The Messenger of Allah said: 'Let men desist from failing to attend the congregation, otherwise I will burn their houses down", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "اسامہ بن زید رضی اللہ عنہما کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  لوگ جماعتوں کے چھو", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Sahih'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 61", "international_number": "795", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "796", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا عَبْدُ الرَّحْمَنِ بْنُ إِبْرَاهِيمَ الدِّمَشْقِيُّ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا الْوَلِيدُ بْنُ مُس", "bengali": "", "english": "Aishah said:\"The Messenger of Allah said: 'If the people knew what (reward) there is in the 'Isha' prayer and fajr prayer, they would come even if they had to crawl", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "ام المؤمنین عائشہ رضی اللہ عنہا کہتی ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  اگر لوگوں کو ع", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Isnaad Sahih'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 62", "international_number": "796", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "797", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو بَكْرِ بْنُ أَبِي شَيْبَةَ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏أَنْبَأَنَا أَبُو مُعَاوِيَةَ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏عَنْ الْأَعْ", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated that Abu Hurairah said:\"The Messenger of Allah said: 'The most burdensome prayers for the hypocrites are the 'Isha' prayer and the Fajr prayer. If only they knew what (reward) there is in them, they would come to them even if they had to crawl", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "ابوہریرہ رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  منافقین پر سب سے بھاری ع", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Sahih Muslim'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 63", "international_number": "797", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "798", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا عُثْمَانُ بْنُ أَبِي شَيْبَةَ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا إِسْمَاعِيل بْنُ عَيَّاشٍ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏عَنْ عُم", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated from 'Umar bin Khattab that:The Prophet used to say: \"Whoever performs prayer in congregation at the mosque for forty nights, never missing the first Rak'ah of the 'Isha' prayer, Allah will thereby decree for him salvation from the Fire", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "عمر بن خطاب رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  کہ نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم فرماتے تھے:  جس شخص نے مسجد میں", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Mawdu'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Hasan'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Daif'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 64", "international_number": "798", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "799", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو بَكْرِ بْنُ أَبِي شَيْبَةَ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو مُعَاوِيَةَ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏عَنْ الْأَعْم", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated that Abu Hurairah said:\"The Messenger of Allah said: 'When one of you enters the mosque, he is in a state of prayer, so long as the prayer keeps him there, and the angels will send prayer upon anyone of you so long as he remains in the place where he prayed, saying: \"O Allah, forgive him; O Allah, have mercy on him; O Allah, accept his repentance,\" so long as he does not commit Hadath nor disturb anyone", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "ابوہریرہ رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  جب کوئی شخص مسجد میں داخ", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Sahih Bukhari'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 65", "international_number": "799", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "800", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو بَكْرِ بْنُ أَبِي شَيْبَةَ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا شَبَابَةُ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا ابْنُ أَبِ", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated from Abu Hurairah that:The Prophet said: \"A muslim does not regularly attend the mosques to perform prayer and remember Allah, but Allah feels happy with him just as the family of one who is absent feels happy when he comes back to them", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "ابوہریرہ رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  نبی اکرم صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  جو مسلمان مسجد کو نماز او", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Isnaad Sahih'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 66", "international_number": "800", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "801", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا أَحْمَدُ بْنُ سَعِيدٍ الدَّارِمِيُّ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا النَّضْرُ بْنُ شُمَيْلٍ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدّ", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated that 'Abdullah bin 'Amr said:\"We performed the Maghrib (prayer) with the Messenger of Allah, then those who went back went back, and those who stayed, stayed. Then the Messenger of Allah came back in a hurry, out of breath, with his garment pulled up to his knees, and said: 'Be of good cheer, for your Lord has opened one of the gates of heaven and is boasting of you before the angels, saying: \"Look at My slaves; they have fulfilled one obligatory duty and are awaiting another", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "عبداللہ بن عمرو رضی اللہ عنہما کہتے ہیں کہ  ہم نے رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم کے ساتھ مغرب کی نماز", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Sahih'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Isnaad Sahih'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 67", "international_number": "801", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
{"hadithnumber": "802", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنَا أَبُو كُرَيْبٍ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏حَدَّثَنَا رِشْدِينُ بْنُ سَعْدٍ، ‏‏‏‏‏‏عَنْ عَمْرِو بْنِ الْحَارِث", "bengali": "", "english": "It was narrated from Abu Sa'eed that:The Messenger of Allah said: \"If you see a man frequenting the mosques, then bear witness to his faith. Allah says: 'The mosques of Allah shall be maintained only by those who believe in Allah and the Last Day. [At-Taubah:]", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "ابو سعید خدری رضی اللہ عنہ کہتے ہیں کہ  رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا:  جب تم کسی شخص کو مس", "grades": "{'name': 'Al-Albani', 'grade': 'Daif'},{'name': 'Muhammad Fouad Abd al-Baqi', 'grade': 'Daif'},{'name': 'Shuaib Al Arnaut', 'grade': 'Daif'},{'name': 'Zubair Ali Zai', 'grade': 'Isnaad Hasan'}", "reference": "Book 4, Hadith 68", "international_number": "802", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "The Book On The Mosques And The Congregations"}
